  2 var n2i = {

  4 	browser : {}

  7 n2i.browser.opera = /opera/i.test(navigator.userAgent);
  8 n2i.browser.msie = !n2i.browser.opera && /MSIE/.test(navigator.userAgent);
  9 n2i.browser.msie7 = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('MSIE 7')!=-1;
 10 n2i.browser.webkit = navigator.userAgent.indexOf('WebKit')!=-1;
 11 n2i.browser.gecko = !n2i.browser.webkit && navigator.userAgent.indexOf('Gecko')!=-1;

 13 n2i.ELEMENT_NODE=1;
 14 n2i.ATTRIBUTE_NODE=2;
 15 n2i.TEXT_NODE=3;

 17 /** Log something */
 18 n2i.log = function(obj) {
 19 	try {
 20 		console.log(obj);
 21 	} catch (ignore) {};
 22 }

 24 /** Make a string camelized */
 25 n2i.camelize = function(str) {
 26     var oStringList = str.split('-');
 27     if (oStringList.length == 1) return oStringList[0];
 28 
 29     var camelizedString = str.indexOf('-') == 0
 30       ? oStringList[0].charAt(0).toUpperCase() + oStringList[0].substring(1)
 31       : oStringList[0];
 32 
 33     for (var i = 1, len = oStringList.length; i < len; i++) {
 34       var s = oStringList[i];
 35       camelizedString += s.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + s.substring(1);
 36     }
 37 
 38     return camelizedString;
 39 }

 41 n2i.override = function(original,subject) {
 42 	if (subject) {
 43 		for (prop in subject) {
 44 			original[prop] = subject[prop];
 45 		}
 46 	}
 47 	return original;
 48 }

 50 /** Trim whitespace including unicode chars */
 51 n2i.trim = function(str) {
 52 	if (!str) return str;
 53 	return str.replace(/^[\s\x0b\xa0\u2000\u2001\u2002\u2003\u2004\u2005\u2006\u2007\u2008\u2009\u200a\u200b\u2028\u2029\u3000]+|[\s\x0b\xa0\u2000\u2001\u2002\u2003\u2004\u2005\u2006\u2007\u2008\u2009\u200a\u200b\u2028\u2029\u3000]+$/g, '');
 54 }
 55 
 56 n2i.escapeHTML = function(str) {
 57     var div = document.createElement('div');
 58     var text = document.createTextNode(str);
 59     div.appendChild(text);
 60     return div.innerHTML;
 61 }

 63 n2i.isEmpty = function(str) {
 64 	if (str==null || typeof(str)=='undefined') return true;
 65 	return n2i.trim(str).length==0;
 66 }

 68 n2i.isDefined = function(obj) {
 69 	return obj!=null && typeof(obj)!='undefined';
 70 }

 72 n2i.inArray = function(arr,value) {
 73 	for (var i=0; i < arr.length; i++) {
 74 		if (arr[i]==value) return true;
 75 	};
 76 }

 79 n2i.flipInArray = function(arr,value) {
 80 	if (n2i.inArray(arr,value)) {
 81 		n2i.removeFromArray(arr,value);
 82 	} else {
 83 		arr.push(value);
 84 	}
 85 }
 86 
 87 n2i.removeFromArray = function(arr,value) {
 88 	for (var i = arr.length - 1; i >= 0; i--){
 89 		if (arr[i]==value) {
 90 			arr.splice(i,1);
 91 		}
 92 	};
 93 }
 94 
 95 n2i.addToArray = function(arr,value) {
 96 	if (value.constructor==Array) {
 97 		for (var i=0; i < value.length; i++) {
 98 			if (!n2i.inArray(arr,value[i])) {
 99 				arr.push(value);
100 			}
101 		};
102 	} else {
103 		if (!n2i.inArray(arr,value)) {
104 			arr.push(value);
105 		}
106 	}
107 }

109 n2i.scrollTo = function(element) {
110 	element = $(element);
111 	if (element) {
112 		var pos = element.cumulativeOffset();
113 		window.scrollTo(pos.left, pos.top-50);
114 	}
115 }

117 /********************* Style ********************/
118 
119 n2i.getStyle = function(element, style) {
120 	element = $(element);
121 	var cameled = n2i.camelize(style);
122 	var value = element.style[cameled];
123 	if (!value) {
124 		if (document.defaultView && document.defaultView.getComputedStyle) {
125 			var css = document.defaultView.getComputedStyle(element, null);
126 			value = css ? css.getPropertyValue(style) : null;
127 		} else if (element.currentStyle) {
128 			value = element.currentStyle[cameled];
129 		}
130 	}
131 	if (window.opera && ['left', 'top', 'right', 'bottom'].include(style)) {
132 		if (n2i.getStyle(element, 'position') == 'static') value = 'auto';
133 	}
134 	return value == 'auto' ? null : value;
135 }
136 
137 n2i.setOpacity = function(element,opacity) {
138 	if (n2i.browser.msie) {
139 		if (opacity==1) {
140 			element.style['filter']=null;
141 		} else {
142 			element.style['filter']='alpha(opacity='+(opacity*100)+')';
143 		}
144 	} else {
145 		element.style['opacity']=opacity;
146 	}
147 }
148 
149 n2i.copyStyle = function(source,target,styles) {
150 	styles.each(function(s) {
151 		var r = source.getStyle(s);
152 		if (r) target.style[s] = source.getStyle(s);
153 	});
154 }

176 n2i.getFrameDocument = function(frame) {
177     if (frame.contentDocument) {
178         return frame.contentDocument;
179     } else if (frame.contentWindow) {
180         return frame.contentWindow.document;
181     } else if (frame.document) {
182         return frame.document;
183     }

188 n2i.getScrollTop = function() {
189 	if (self.pageYOffset) {
190 		return self.pageYOffset;
191 	} else if (document.documentElement && document.documentElement.scrollTop) {
192 		return document.documentElement.scrollTop;
193 	} else if (document.body) {
194 		return document.body.scrollTop;
195 	}
196 }
197 
198 n2i.getScrollLeft = function() {
199 	if (self.pageYOffset) {
200 		return self.pageXOffset;
201 	} else if (document.documentElement && document.documentElement.scrollTop) {
202 		return document.documentElement.scrollLeft;
203 	} else if (document.body) {
204 		return document.body.scrollLeft;
205 	}
206 }
207 
208 n2i.getInnerHeight = function() {
209 	var y;
210 	if (self.innerHeight) {
211 		return self.innerHeight;
212 	} else if (document.documentElement && document.documentElement.clientHeight) {
213 		return document.documentElement.clientHeight;
214 	} else if (document.body) {
215 		return document.body.clientHeight;
216 	}
217 }
218 
219 n2i.getInnerWidth = function() {
220 	if (self.innerHeight) {
221 		return self.innerWidth;
222 	} else if (document.documentElement && document.documentElement.clientHeight) {
223 		return document.documentElement.clientWidth;
224 	} else if (document.body) {
225 		return document.body.clientWidth;
226 	}
227 }
228 
229 n2i.getDocumentHeight = function() {
230 	if (window.scrollMaxY && window.innerHeight) {
231 		return window.scrollMaxY+window.innerHeight;
232 	} else {
233 		return Math.max(document.body.clientHeight,document.documentElement.clientHeight,document.documentElement.scrollHeight);
234 	}
235 }

237 /** @constructor */
238 n2i.Preloader = function(options) {
239 	this.options = options || {};
240 	this.delegate = {};
241 	this.images = [];
242 	this.loaded = 0;
243 }
244 
245 n2i.Preloader.prototype = {
246 	addImages : function(imageOrImages) {
247 		if (typeof(imageOrImages)=='object') {
248 			for (var i=0; i < imageOrImages.length; i++) {
249 				this.images.push(imageOrImages[i]);
250 			};
251 		} else {
252 			this.images.push(imageOrImages);
253 		}
254 	},
255 	setDelegate : function(d) {
256 		this.delegate = d;
257 	},
258 	load : function() {
259 		var self = this;
260 		this.obs = [];
261 		for (var i=0; i < this.images.length; i++) {
262 			var img = new Image();
263 			img.n2iPreloaderIndex = i;
264 			img.onload = function() {self.imageChanged(this.n2iPreloaderIndex,'imageDidLoad')};
265 			img.onerror = function() {self.imageChanged(this.n2iPreloaderIndex,'imageDidGiveError')};
266 			img.onabort = function() {self.imageChanged(this.n2iPreloaderIndex,'imageDidAbort')};
267 			img.src = (this.options.context ? this.options.context : '')+this.images[i];
268 			this.obs.push(img);
269 		};
270 	},
271 	imageChanged : function(index,method) {
272 		this.loaded++;
273 		if (this.delegate[method]) {
274 			this.delegate[method](this.loaded,this.images.length,index);
275 		}
276 		if (this.loaded==this.images.length && this.delegate.allImagesDidLoad) {
277 			this.delegate.allImagesDidLoad();
278 		}
279 	}
280 }

282 /* @namespace */
283 n2i.cookie = {
284 	set : function(name,value,days) {
285 		if (days) {
286 			var date = new Date();
287 			date.setTime(date.getTime()+(days*24*60*60*1000));
288 			var expires = "; expires="+date.toGMTString();
289 		}
290 		else var expires = "";
291 		document.cookie = name+"="+value+expires+"; path=/";
292 	},
293 	get : function(name) {
294 		var nameEQ = name + "=";
295 		var ca = document.cookie.split(';');
296 		for(var i=0;i < ca.length;i++) {
297 			var c = ca[i];
298 			while (c.charAt(0)==' ') c = c.substring(1,c.length);
299 			if (c.indexOf(nameEQ) == 0) return c.substring(nameEQ.length,c.length);
300 		}
301 		return null;
302 	},
303 	clear : function(name) {
304 		this.set(name,"",-1);
305 	}
306 }

310 n2i.URL = function(url) {
311 	this.url = url || '';
312 }

314 n2i.URL.prototype = {
315 	addParameter : function(key,value) {
316 		this.url+=this.url.indexOf('?')!=-1 ? '&' : '?';
317 		this.url+=key+'='+(n2i.isDefined(value) ? value : '');
318 	},
319 	toString : function() {
320 		return this.url;
321 	}
322 }

324 /* @namespace */
325 n2i.location = {
326 	getParameter : function(name) {
327 		var parms = n2i.location.getParameters();
328 		for (var i=0; i < parms.length; i++) {
329 			if (parms[i].name==name) {
330 				return parms[i].value;
331 			}
332 		};
333 		return null;
334 	},
335 	setParameter : function(name,value) {
336 		var parms = n2i.location.getParameters();
337 		var found = false;
338 		for (var i=0; i < parms.length; i++) {
339 			if (parms[i].name==name) {
340 				parms[i].value=value;
341 				found=true;
342 				break;
343 			}
344 		};
345 		if (!found) {
346 			parms.push({name:name,value:value});
347 		}
348 		n2i.location.setParameters(parms);
349 	},
350 	setParameters : function(parms) {
351 		var query = '';
352 		for (var i=0; i < parms.length; i++) {
353 			query+= i==0 ? '?' : '&';
354 			query+=parms[i].name+'='+parms[i].value;
355 		};
356 		document.location.search=query;
357 	},
358 	getBoolean : function(name) {
359 		var value = n2i.location.getParameter(name);
360 		return (value=='true' || value=='1');
361 	},
362 	getParameters : function() {
363 		var items = document.location.search.substring(1).split('&');
364 		var parsed = [];
365 		for( var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
366 			var item = items[i].split('=');
367 			var name = unescape(item[0]).replace(/^\s*|\s*$/g,"");
368 			var value = unescape(item[1]).replace(/^\s*|\s*$/g,"");
369 			if (name) {
370 				parsed.push({name:name,value:value});
371 			}
372 		};
373 		return parsed;
374 	}	
375 };

380 n2i.ani = n2i.animate = function(element,style,value,duration,delegate) {
381 	n2i.animation.get(element).animate(null,value,style,duration,delegate);
382 }
383 
384 /* @namespace */
385 n2i.animation = {
386 	objects : {},
387 	running : false,
388 	latestId : 0,
389 	get : function(element) {
390 		element = $(element);
391 		if (!element.n2iAnimationId) element.n2iAnimationId = this.latestId++;
392 		if (!this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId]) {
393 			this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId] = new n2i.animation.Item(element);
394 		}
395 		return this.objects[element.n2iAnimationId];
396 	},
397 	start : function() {
398 		if (!this.running) {
399 			n2i.animation.render();
400 		}
401 	}
402 };
403 
404 n2i.animation.render = function(element) {
405 	this.running = true;
406 	var next = false;
407 	var stamp = new Date().getTime();
408 	for (id in this.objects) {
409 		var obj = this.objects[id];
410 		if (obj.work) {
411 			for (var i=0; i < obj.work.length; i++) {
412 				var work = obj.work[i];
413 				if (work.finished) continue;
414 				var place = (stamp-work.start)/(work.end-work.start);
415 				if (place<0) {
416 					next=true;
417 					continue;
418 				}
419 				else if (isNaN(place)) place = 1;
420 				else if (place>1) place=1;
421 				else if (place<1) next=true;
422 				var v = place;
423 				if (work.delegate && work.delegate.ease) {
424 					v = work.delegate.ease(v);
425 				}
426 				var value = null;
427 				if (!work.css) {
428 					obj.element[work.property] = Math.round(work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v);
429 				} else if (work.to.red!=null) {
430 					var red = Math.round(work.from.red+(work.to.red-work.from.red)*v);
431 					var green = Math.round(work.from.green+(work.to.green-work.from.green)*v);
432 					var blue = Math.round(work.from.blue+(work.to.blue-work.from.blue)*v);
433 					value = 'rgb('+red+','+green+','+blue+')';
434 					obj.element.style[work.property]=value;
435 				} else if (n2i.browser.msie && work.property=='opacity') {
436 					var opacity = (work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v);
437 					if (opacity==1) {
438 						obj.element.style['filter']='';
439 					} else {
440 						obj.element.style['filter']='alpha(opacity='+(opacity*100)+')';
441 					}
442 				} else {
443 					value = new String(work.from+(work.to-work.from)*v)+(work.unit!=null ? work.unit : '');
444 					obj.element.style[work.property]=value;
445 				}
446 				if (place==1) {
447 					work.finished = true;
448 					if (work.delegate && work.delegate.onComplete) {
449 						work.delegate.onComplete();
450 					} else if (work.delegate && work.delegate.hideOnComplete) {
451 						obj.element.style.display='none';
452 					}
453 				}
454 			};
455 		}
456 	}
457 	if (next) {
458 		window.setTimeout(function() {
459 			n2i.animation.render();
460 		},0);
461 	} else {
462 		this.running = false;
463 	}
464 	//window.status = this.running;
465 }
466 
467 n2i.animation.parseStyle = function(value) {
468 	var parsed = {type:null,value:null,unit:null};
469 	var match;
470 	if (!n2i.isDefined(value)) {
471 		return parsed;
472 	} else if (!isNaN(value)) {
473 		parsed.value=parseFloat(value);
474 	} else if (match=value.match(/([\-]?[0-9\.]+)(px|pt|%)/)) {
475 		parsed.type = 'length';
476 		parsed.value = parseFloat(match[1]);
477 		parsed.unit = match[2];
478 	} else if (match=value.match(/rgb\(([0-9]+),[ ]?([0-9]+),[ ]?([0-9]+)\)/)) {
479 		parsed.type = 'color';
480 		parsed.value = {
481 			red:parseInt(match[1]),
482 			green:parseInt(match[2]),
483 			blue:parseInt(match[3])
484 		};
485 	} else {
486 		var color = new n2i.Color(value);
487 		if (color.ok) {
488 			parsed.value = {
489 				red:color.r,
490 				green:color.g,
491 				blue:color.b
492 			};
493 		}
494 	}
495 	return parsed;
496 }
497 
498 /********************************* Item **********************************/
499 
500 n2i.animation.Item = function(element) {
501 	this.element = element;
502 	this.work = [];
503 }
504 
505 n2i.animation.Item.prototype.animate = function(from,to,property,duration,delegate) {
506 	var css = true;
507 	if (property=='scrollLeft') {
508 		css = false;
509 	}
510 	
511 	var work = this.getWork(css ? n2i.camelize(property) : property);
512 	work.delegate = delegate;
513 	work.finished = false;
514 	work.css = css;
515 	if (from!=null) {
516 		work.from = from;
517 	} else if (work.css && n2i.browser.msie && property=='opacity') {
518 		work.from = this.getIEOpacity(this.element);
519 	} else if (work.css) {
520 		var style = n2i.getStyle(this.element,property);
521 		var parsedStyle = n2i.animation.parseStyle(style);
522 		work.from = parsedStyle.value;
523 	} else {
524 		work.from = this.element[property];
525 	}
526 	if (work.css) {
527 		var parsed = n2i.animation.parseStyle(to);
528 		work.to = parsed.value;
529 		work.unit = parsed.unit;
530 	} else {
531 		work.to = to;
532 		work.unit = null;
533 	}
534 	work.start = new Date().getTime();
535 	if (delegate && delegate.delay) work.start+=delegate.delay;
536 	work.end = work.start+duration;
537 	n2i.animation.start();
538 }
539 
540 n2i.animation.Item.prototype.getIEOpacity = function(element) {
541 	var filter = n2i.getStyle(element,'filter').toLowerCase();
542 	var match;
543 	if (match = filter.match(/opacity=([0-9]+)/)) {
544 		return parseFloat(match[1])/100;
545 	} else {
546 		return 1;
547 	}
548 }
549 
550 n2i.animation.Item.prototype.getWork = function(property) {
551 	for (var i=0; i < this.work.length; i++) {
552 		if (this.work[i].property==property) {
553 			return this.work[i];
554 		}
555 	};
556 	var work = {property:property};
557 	this.work[this.work.length] = work;
558 	return work;
559 }
560 
561 /************************************** Loop **********************************/
562 
563 n2i.animation.Loop = function(recipe) {
564 	this.recipe = recipe;
565 	this.position = -1;
566 	this.running = false;
567 }
568 
569 n2i.animation.Loop.prototype.next = function() {
570 	this.position++;
571 	if (this.position>=this.recipe.length) {
572 		this.position = 0;
573 	}
574 	var item = this.recipe[this.position];
575 	if (typeof(item)=='function') {
576 		item();
577 	} else if (item.element) {
578 		n2i.ani(item.element,item.property,item.value,item.duration,{ease:item.ease});
579 	}
580 	var self = this;
581 	var time = item.duration || 0;
582 	window.setTimeout(function() {self.next()},time);
583 }
584 
585 n2i.animation.Loop.prototype.start = function() {
586 	this.running=true;
587 	this.next();
588 }

598         color_string = color_string.substr(1,6);

601     color_string = color_string.replace(/ /g,'');

603

605     // and overwrite the input
606     var simple_colors = {

624         cornflowerblue: '6495ed',
625         cornsilk: 'fff8dc',
626         crimson: 'dc143c',
627         cyan: '00ffff',
628         darkblue: '00008b',
629         darkcyan: '008b8b',
630         darkgoldenrod: 'b8860b',
631         darkgray: 'a9a9a9',
632         darkgreen: '006400',
633         darkkhaki: 'bdb76b',
634         darkmagenta: '8b008b',
635         darkolivegreen: '556b2f',
636         darkorange: 'ff8c00',
637         darkorchid: '9932cc',
638         darkred: '8b0000',
639         darksalmon: 'e9967a',

641         darkslateblue: '483d8b',
642         darkslategray: '2f4f4f',

741         tomato: 'ff6347',
742         turquoise: '40e0d0',
743         violet: 'ee82ee',
744         violetred: 'd02090',
745         wheat: 'f5deb3',
746         white: 'ffffff',
747         whitesmoke: 'f5f5f5',
748         yellow: 'ffff00',
749         yellowgreen: '9acd32'
750     };
751     for (var key in simple_colors) {
752         if (color_string == key) {
753             color_string = simple_colors[key];
754         }
755     }
756     // emd of simple type-in colors
757 
758     // array of color definition objects
759     var color_defs = [
760         {
761             re: /^rgb\((\d{1,3}),\s*(\d{1,3}),\s*(\d{1,3})\)$/,
762             example: ['rgb(123, 234, 45)', 'rgb(255,234,245)'],
763             process: function (bits){
764                 return [
765                     parseInt(bits[1]),
766                     parseInt(bits[2]),
767                     parseInt(bits[3])
768                 ];
769             }
770         },
771         {
772             re: /^(\w{2})(\w{2})(\w{2})$/,
773             example: ['#00ff00', '336699'],
774             process: function (bits){
775                 return [
776                     parseInt(bits[1], 16),
777                     parseInt(bits[2], 16),
778                     parseInt(bits[3], 16)
779                 ];
780             }
781         },
782         {
783             re: /^(\w{1})(\w{1})(\w{1})$/,
784             example: ['#fb0', 'f0f'],
785             process: function (bits){
786                 return [
787                     parseInt(bits[1] + bits[1], 16),
788                     parseInt(bits[2] + bits[2], 16),
789                     parseInt(bits[3] + bits[3], 16)
790                 ];
791             }
792         }
793     ];
794 
795     // search through the definitions to find a match
796     for (var i = 0; i < color_defs.length; i++) {
797         var re = color_defs[i].re;
798         var processor = color_defs[i].process;
799         var bits = re.exec(color_string);
800         if (bits) {
801             channels = processor(bits);
802             this.r = channels[0];
803             this.g = channels[1];
804             this.b = channels[2];
805             this.ok = true;
806         }
807 
808     }
809 
810     // validate/cleanup values
811     this.r = (this.r < 0 || isNaN(this.r)) ? 0 : ((this.r > 255) ? 255 : this.r);
812     this.g = (this.g < 0 || isNaN(this.g)) ? 0 : ((this.g > 255) ? 255 : this.g);
813     this.b = (this.b < 0 || isNaN(this.b)) ? 0 : ((this.b > 255) ? 255 : this.b);
814 
815     // some getters
816     this.toRGB = function () {
817         return 'rgb(' + this.r + ', ' + this.g + ', ' + this.b + ')';
818     }
819     this.toHex = function () {
820         var r = this.r.toString(16);
821         var g = this.g.toString(16);
822         var b = this.b.toString(16);
823         if (r.length == 1) r = '0' + r;
824         if (g.length == 1) g = '0' + g;
825         if (b.length == 1) b = '0' + b;
826         return '#' + r + g + b;
827     }
828 
829 }

832 n2i.ease = {
833 	slowFastSlow : function(val) {
834 		var a = 1.6;
835 		var b = 1.4;
836 		return -1*Math.pow(Math.cos((Math.PI/2)*Math.pow(val,a)),Math.pow(Math.PI,b))+1;
837 	},
838 	fastSlow : function(val) {
839 		var a = .5;
840 		var b = .7
841 		return -1*Math.pow(Math.cos((Math.PI/2)*Math.pow(val,a)),Math.pow(Math.PI,b))+1;
842 	},
843 	elastic : function(t) {
844 		return 1 - n2i.ease.elastic2(1-t);
845 	},
846 
847 	elastic2 : function (t, a, p) {
848 		if (t<=0 || t>=1) return t;
849 		if (!p) p=0.45;
850 		var s;
851 		if (!a || a < 1) {
852 			a=1;
853 			s=p/4;
854 		} else {
855 			s = p/(2*Math.PI) * Math.asin (1/a);
856 		}
857 		return -(a*Math.pow(2,10*(t-=1)) * Math.sin( (t-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p ));
858 	},
859 	bounce : function(t) {
860 		if (t < (1/2.75)) {
861 			return 7.5625*t*t;
862 		} else if (t < (2/2.75)) {
863 			return (7.5625*(t-=(1.5/2.75))*t + .75);
864 		} else if (t < (2.5/2.75)) {
865 			return (7.5625*(t-=(2.25/2.75))*t + .9375);
866 		} else {
867 			return (7.5625*(t-=(2.625/2.75))*t + .984375);
868 		}
869 	},
870 	
871 	linear: function(/* Decimal? */n){
872 		// summary: A linear easing function
873 		return n;
874 	},
875 
876 	quadIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
877 		return Math.pow(n, 2);
878 	},
879 
880 	quadOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
881 		return n * (n-2) * -1;
882 	},
883 
884 	quadInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
885 		n=n*2;
886 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 2) / 2; }
887 		return -1 * ((--n)*(n-2) - 1) / 2;
888 	},
889 
890 	cubicIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
891 		return Math.pow(n, 3);
892 	},
893 
894 	cubicOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
895 		return Math.pow(n-1, 3) + 1;
896 	},
897 
898 	cubicInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
899 		n=n*2;
900 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 3) / 2; }
901 		n-=2;
902 		return (Math.pow(n, 3) + 2) / 2;
903 	},
904 
905 	quartIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
906 		return Math.pow(n, 4);
907 	},
908 
909 	quartOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
910 		return -1 * (Math.pow(n-1, 4) - 1);
911 	},
912 
913 	quartInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
914 		n=n*2;
915 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 4) / 2; }
916 		n-=2;
917 		return -1/2 * (Math.pow(n, 4) - 2);
918 	},
919 
920 	quintIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
921 		return Math.pow(n, 5);
922 	},
923 
924 	quintOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
925 		return Math.pow(n-1, 5) + 1;
926 	},
927 
928 	quintInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
929 		n=n*2;
930 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(n, 5) / 2; };
931 		n-=2;
932 		return (Math.pow(n, 5) + 2) / 2;
933 	},
934 
935 	sineIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
936 		return -1 * Math.cos(n * (Math.PI/2)) + 1;
937 	},
938 
939 	sineOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
940 		return Math.sin(n * (Math.PI/2));
941 	},
942 
943 	sineInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
944 		return -1 * (Math.cos(Math.PI*n) - 1) / 2;
945 	},
946 
947 	expoIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
948 		return (n==0) ? 0 : Math.pow(2, 10 * (n - 1));
949 	},
950 
951 	expoOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
952 		return (n==1) ? 1 : (-1 * Math.pow(2, -10 * n) + 1);
953 	},
954 
955 	expoInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
956 		if(n==0){ return 0; }
957 		if(n==1){ return 1; }
958 		n = n*2;
959 		if(n<1){ return Math.pow(2, 10 * (n-1)) / 2; }
960 		--n;
961 		return (-1 * Math.pow(2, -10 * n) + 2) / 2;
962 	},
963 
964 	circIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
965 		return -1 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) - 1);
966 	},
967 
968 	circOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
969 		n = n-1;
970 		return Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2));
971 	},
972 
973 	circInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
974 		n = n*2;
975 		if(n<1){ return -1/2 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) - 1); }
976 		n-=2;
977 		return 1/2 * (Math.sqrt(1 - Math.pow(n, 2)) + 1);
978 	},
979 
980 	backIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
981 		var s = 1.70158;
982 		return Math.pow(n, 2) * ((s+1)*n - s);
983 	},
984 
985 	backOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
986 		// summary: an easing function that pops past the range briefly, and 
987 		// 	slowly comes back. 
988 		n = n - 1;
989 		var s = 1.70158;
990 		return Math.pow(n, 2) * ((s + 1) * n + s) + 1;
991 	},
992 
993 	backInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
994 		var s = 1.70158 * 1.525;
995 		n = n*2;
996 		if(n < 1){ return (Math.pow(n, 2)*((s+1)*n - s))/2; }
997 		n-=2;
998 		return (Math.pow(n, 2)*((s+1)*n + s) + 2)/2;
999 	},
1000 
1001 	elasticIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1002 		if(n==0){ return 0; }
1003 		if(n==1){ return 1; }
1004 		var p = .3;
1005 		var s = p/4;
1006 		n = n - 1;
1007 		return -1 * Math.pow(2,10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p);
1008 	},
1009 
1010 	elasticOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1011 		// summary: An easing function that elasticly snaps around the target value, near the end of the Animation
1012 		if(n==0) return 0;
1013 		if(n==1) return 1;
1014 		var p = .3;
1015 		var s = p/4;
1016 		return Math.pow(2,-10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p) + 1;
1017 	},
1018 
1019 	elasticInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1020 		// summary: An easing function that elasticly snaps around the value, near the beginning and end of the Animation		
1021 		if(n==0) return 0;
1022 		n = n*2;
1023 		if(n==2) return 1;
1024 		var p = .3*1.5;
1025 		var s = p/4;
1026 		if(n<1){
1027 			n-=1;
1028 			return -.5*(Math.pow(2,10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p));
1029 		}
1030 		n-=1;
1031 		return .5*(Math.pow(2,-10*n) * Math.sin((n-s)*(2*Math.PI)/p)) + 1;
1032 	},
1033 
1034 	bounceIn: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1035 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" near the beginning of an Animation
1036 		return (1 - n2i.ease.bounceOut(1-n)); // Decimal
1037 	},
1038 
1039 	bounceOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1040 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" near the end of an Animation
1041 		var s=7.5625;
1042 		var p=2.75;
1043 		var l; 
1044 		if(n < (1 / p)){
1045 			l = s*Math.pow(n, 2);
1046 		}else if(n < (2 / p)){
1047 			n -= (1.5 / p);
1048 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .75;
1049 		}else if(n < (2.5 / p)){
1050 			n -= (2.25 / p);
1051 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .9375;
1052 		}else{
1053 			n -= (2.625 / p);
1054 			l = s * Math.pow(n, 2) + .984375;
1055 		}
1056 		return l;
1057 	},
1058 
1059 	bounceInOut: function(/* Decimal? */n){
1060 		// summary: An easing function that "bounces" at the beginning and end of the Animation
1061 		if(n<0.5){ return n2i.ease.bounceIn(n*2) / 2; }
1062 		return (n2i.ease.bounceOut(n*2-1) / 2) + 0.5; // Decimal
1063 	}

1066 WysiHat.Editor = {
1067   /**
1068    *  WysiHat.Editor.attach(textarea)
1069    *  - textarea (String | Element): an id or DOM node of the textarea that
1070    *  you want to convert to rich text.
1071    *
1072    *  Creates a new editor for the textarea.
1073    **/
1074   attach: function(textarea) {
1075     textarea = $(textarea);
1076     textarea.hide();
1077 
1078     return WysiHat.iFrame.create(textarea, function(editArea) {
1079       var document = editArea.getDocument();
1080       var window = editArea.getWindow();
1081       editArea.load();
1082 
1083       Event.observe(window, 'focus', function(event) { editArea.focus(); });
1084       Event.observe(window, 'blur', function(event) { editArea.blur(); });
1085 
1086 
1087       Event.observe(document, 'mouseup', function(event) {
1088         editArea.fire("wysihat:mouseup");
1089       });
1090 
1091       Event.observe(document, 'mousemove', function(event) {
1092         editArea.fire("wysihat:mousemove");
1093       });
1094 
1095       Event.observe(document, 'keypress', function(event) {
1096         editArea.fire("wysihat:change");
1097         editArea.fire("wysihat:keypress");
1098       });
1099 
1100       Event.observe(document, 'keyup', function(event) {
1101         editArea.fire("wysihat:change");
1102         editArea.fire("wysihat:keyup");
1103       });
1104 
1105       Event.observe(document, 'keydown', function(event) {
1106         if (event.keyCode == 86)
1107           editArea.fire("wysihat:paste");
1108       });
1109 
1110       Event.observe(window, 'paste', function(event) {
1111         editArea.fire("wysihat:paste");
1112       });
1113 
1114 
1115       editArea.observe("wysihat:change", function(event) {
1116         event.target.save();
1117       });
1118 
1119         editArea.fire("wysihat:loaded"); // HACK
1120       //editArea.focus(); HACK!
1121     });
1122   }
1123 };

1125 /**
1126  * mixin WysiHat.Commands
1127  *
1128  *  Methods will be mixed into the editor element. Most of these
1129  *  methods will be used to bind to button clicks or key presses.
1130  *
1131  *  var editor = WysiHat.Editor.attach(textarea);
1132  *  $('bold_button').observe('click', function(event) {
1133  *    editor.boldSelection();
1134  *    Event.stop(event);
1135  *  });
1136  *
1137  *  In this example, it is important to stop the click event so you don't
1138  *  lose your current selection.
1139  **/
1140 WysiHat.Commands = {
1141   /**
1142    * WysiHat.Commands#boldSelection() -> undefined
1143    *  Bolds the current selection.
1144    **/
1145   boldSelection: function() {
1146     this.execCommand('bold', false, null);
1147   },
1148 
1149   /**
1150    * WysiHat.Commands#underlineSelection() -> undefined
1151    *  Underlines the current selection.
1152    **/
1153   underlineSelection: function() {
1154     this.execCommand('underline', false, null);
1155   },
1156 
1157   /**
1158    * WysiHat.Commands#italicSelection() -> undefined
1159    *  Italicizes the current selection.
1160    **/
1161   italicSelection: function() {
1162     this.execCommand('italic', false, null);
1163   },
1164 
1165   /**
1166    * WysiHat.Commands#italicSelection() -> undefined
1167    *  Strikethroughs the current selection.
1168    **/
1169   strikethroughSelection: function() {
1170     this.execCommand('strikethrough', false, null);
1171   },
1172 
1173   /**
1174    * WysiHat.Commands#italicSelection() -> undefined
1175    *  Blockquotes the current selection.
1176    **/
1177   blockquoteSelection: function() {
1178     this.execCommand('blockquote', false, null);
1179   },
1180 
1181   /**
1182    * WysiHat.Commands#colorSelection(color) -> undefined
1183    *  - color (String): a color name or hexadecimal value
1184    *  Sets the foreground color of the current selection.
1185    **/
1186   colorSelection: function(color) {
1187     this.execCommand('forecolor', false, color);
1188   },
1189 
1190   /**
1191    * WysiHat.Commands#linkSelection(url) -> undefined
1192    *  - url (String): value for href
1193    *  Wraps the current selection in a link.
1194    **/
1195   linkSelection: function(url) {
1196     this.execCommand('createLink', false, url);
1197   },
1198 
1199   /**
1200    * WysiHat.Commands#insertOrderedList() -> undefined
1201    *  Formats current selection as an ordered list. If the selection is empty
1202    *  a new list is inserted.
1203    **/
1204   insertOrderedList: function() {
1205     this.execCommand('insertorderedlist', false, null);
1206   },
1207 
1208   /**
1209    * WysiHat.Commands#insertUnorderedList() -> undefined
1210    *  Formats current selection as an unordered list. If the selection is empty
1211    *  a new list is inserted.
1212    **/
1213   insertUnorderedList: function() {
1214     this.execCommand('insertunorderedlist', false, null);
1215   },
1216 
1217   /**
1218    * WysiHat.Commands#insertImage(url) -> undefined
1219    *  - url (String): value for src
1220    *  Insert an image at the insertion point with the given url.
1221    **/
1222   insertImage: function(url) {
1223     this.execCommand('insertImage', false, url);
1224   },
1225 
1226   /**
1227    * WysiHat.Commands#insertHTML(html) -> undefined
1228    *  - html (String): HTML or plain text
1229    *  Insert HTML at the insertion point.
1230    **/
1231   insertHTML: function(html) {
1232     if (Prototype.Browser.IE) {
1233       var range = this._selection.getRange();
1234       range.pasteHTML(html);
1235       range.collapse(false);
1236       range.select();
1237     } else {
1238       this.execCommand('insertHTML', false, html);
1239     }
1240   },
1241 
1242   /**
1243    * WysiHat.Commands#execCommand(command[, ui = false][, value = null]) -> undefined
1244    *  - command (String): Command to execute
1245    *  - ui (Boolean): Boolean flag for showing UI. Currenty this not
1246    *  implemented by any browser. Just use false.
1247    *  - value (String): Value to pass to command
1248    *  A simple delegation method to the documents execCommand method.
1249    **/
1250   execCommand: function(command, ui, value) {
1251     var document = this.getDocument();
1252     document.execCommand(command, ui, value);
1253   },
1254 
1255   queryStateCommands: $A(['bold', 'italic', 'underline', 'strikethrough']),
1256 
1257   /**
1258    * WysiHat.Commands#queryCommandState(state) -> Boolean
1259    *  - state (String): bold, italic, underline, etc
1260    *  Determines whether the current selection has the given state.
1261    *  queryCommandState('bold') would return true if the selected text
1262    *  is bold.
1263    *
1264    * You can extend this behavior by adding a custom method to the editor
1265    * element, queryCustom(). However this API is not final.
1266    * queryCommandState('link') would call queryLink().
1267    **/
1268   queryCommandState: function(state) {
1269     var document = this.getDocument();
1270 
1271     if (this.queryStateCommands.include(state))
1272       return document.queryCommandState(state);
1273     else if ((f = this['query' + state.capitalize()]))
1274       return f.bind(this).call();
1275     else
1276       return false;
1277   }
1278 };
1279 /**
1280  * mixin WysiHat.Persistence
1281  *
1282  *  Methods will be mixed into the editor element. These methods deal with
1283  *  extracting and filtering content going in and out of the editor.
1284  */
1285 WysiHat.Persistence = (function() {
1286   /**
1287    * WysiHat.Persistence#outputFilter(text) -> String
1288    *  - text (String): HTML string
1289    *
1290    *  Use to filter content coming out of the editor. By default it calls
1291    *  text.format_html_output. This method has been extract so you can override
1292    *  it and provide your own custom output filter.
1293    */
1294   function outputFilter(text) {
1295     return text.format_html_output();
1296   }
1297 
1298   /**
1299    * WysiHat.Persistence#inputFilter(text) -> String
1300    *  - text (String): HTML string
1301    *
1302    *  Use to filter content going into the editor. By default it calls
1303    *  text.format_html_input. This method has been extract so you can override
1304    *  it and provide your own custom input filter.
1305    */
1306   function inputFilter(text) {
1307     return text.format_html_input();
1308   }
1309 
1310   /**
1311    * WysiHat.Persistence#content() -> String
1312    *  Returns the editors HTML contents. The contents are first passed
1313    *  through outputFilter.
1314    *
1315    *  You can replace the generic outputFilter with your own function. The
1316    *  default behavior is to use String#format_html_output.
1317    *
1318    *  editor.outputFilter = function(text) {
1319    *    return MyUtils.format_and_santize(text);
1320    *  };
1321    **/
1322   function content() {
1323     return this.outputFilter(this.rawContent());
1324   }
1325 
1326   /**
1327    * WysiHat.Persistence#setContent(text) -> undefined
1328    *  - text (String): HTML string
1329    *
1330    *  Replaces editor's entire contents with the given HTML. The contents are
1331    *  first passed through inputFilter.
1332    *
1333    *  You can replace the generic inputFilter with your own function. The
1334    *  default behavior is to use String#format_html_input.
1335    *
1336    *  editor.inputFilter = function(text) {
1337    *    return MyUtils.format_and_santize(text);
1338    *  };
1339    **/
1340   function setContent(text) {
1341     this.setRawContent(this.inputFilter(text));
1342   }
1343 
1344   /**
1345    * WysiHat.Persistence#save() -> undefined
1346    *  Saves editors contents back out to the textarea.
1347    **/
1348   function save() {
1349     this.textarea.value = this.content();
1350   }
1351 
1352   /**
1353    * WysiHat.Persistence#load() -> undefined
1354    *  Loads textarea contents into editor.
1355    **/
1356    function load() {
1357      this.setContent(this.textarea.value);
1358   }
1359 
1360   /**
1361    * WysiHat.Persistence#reload() -> undefined
1362    *  Saves current contents and loads contents into editor.
1363    **/
1364   function reload() {
1365     this.selection.setBookmark();
1366     this.save();
1367     this.load();
1368     this.selection.moveToBookmark();
1369   }
1370 
1371   return {
1372     outputFilter: outputFilter,
1373     inputFilter:  inputFilter,
1374     content:      content,
1375     setContent:   setContent,
1376     save:         save,
1377     load:         load,
1378     reload:       reload
1379   };
1380 })();
1381 /**
1382  * mixin WysiHat.Window
1383  *
1384  *  Methods will be mixed into the editor element. These methods handle window
1385  *  events such as focus and blur events on the editor.
1386  */
1387 WysiHat.Window = (function() {
1388   /**
1389    * WysiHat.Window#getDocument() -> Document
1390    *  Cross browser method to return the iFrame's document.
1391    *  You should not need to access this directly, and this API is not final.
1392    */
1393   function getDocument() {
1394     return this.contentDocument || this.contentWindow.document;
1395   }
1396 
1397   /**
1398    * WysiHat.Window#getWindow() -> Window
1399    *  Cross browser method to return the iFrame's window.
1400    *  You should not need to access this directly, and this API is not final.
1401    */
1402   function getWindow() {
1403     if (this.contentDocument)
1404       return this.contentDocument.defaultView;
1405     else if (this.contentWindow.document)
1406       return this.contentWindow;
1407     else
1408       return null;
1409   }
1410 
1411   /**
1412    * WysiHat.Window#focus() -> undefined
1413    *  binds observers to mouseup, mousemove, keypress, and keyup on focus
1414    **/
1415   function focus() {
1416     this.getWindow().focus();
1417 
1418     if (this.hasFocus)
1419       return;
1420 
1421     this.hasFocus = true;
1422   }
1423 
1424   /**
1425    * WysiHat.Window#blur() -> undefined
1426    *  removes observers to mouseup, mousemove, keypress, and keyup on blur
1427    **/
1428   function blur() {
1429     this.hasFocus = false;
1430   }
1431 
1432   return {
1433     getDocument: getDocument,
1434     getWindow: getWindow,
1435     focus: focus,
1436     blur: blur
1437   };
1438 })();

1457 WysiHat.iFrame.Methods = {
1458   attach: function(element, callback) {
1459     this.textarea = element;
1460 
1461     this.observe('load', function() {
1462       function setDocumentStyles(document, styles) {
1463         if (Prototype.Browser.IE) {
1464           var style = document.createStyleSheet();
1465           style.addRule("body", "border: 0");
1466           style.addRule("p", "margin: 0");
1467 
1468           $H(styles).each(function(pair) {
1469             var value = pair.first().underscore().dasherize() + ": " + pair.last();
1470             style.addRule("body", value);
1471           });
1472         } else if (Prototype.Browser.Opera) {
1473           var style = Element('style').update("p { margin: 0; }");
1474           var head = document.getElementsByTagName('head')[0];
1475           head.appendChild(style);
1476         } else {
1477           Element.setStyle(document.body, styles);
1478         }
1479       }
1480

1482         var document = this.getDocument();
1483       } catch(e) { return; } // No iframe, just stop
1484 
1485       this.selection = new WysiHat.Selection(this);
1486 
1487       if (this.ready && document.designMode == 'on')
1488         return;
1489 
1490       setDocumentStyles(document, WysiHat.Editor.styles || {});
1491 
1492       document.designMode = 'on';
1493       callback(this);
1494       this.ready = true;
1495     });
1496   },

1499     var document = this.getDocument();
1500     return document.body.innerHTML;
1501   },

1504     var document = this.getDocument();
1505     if (document.body)
1506       document.body.innerHTML = text;
1507   }

1509 
1510 Object.extend(String.prototype, (function() {
1511   /**
1512    * String#format_html_output() -> String
1513    *
1514    *  Cleanup browser's HTML mess!
1515    *
1516    *  There is no standard formatting among the major browsers for the rich
1517    *  text output. Safari wraps its line breaks with "div" tags, Firefox puts
1518    *  "br" tags at the end of the line, and other such as Internet Explorer
1519    *  wrap lines in "p" tags.
1520    *
1521    *  The output is a standarizes these inconsistencies and produces a clean
1522    *  result. A single return creates a line break "br" and double returns
1523    *  create a new paragraph. This is similar to how Textile and Markdown
1524    *  handle whitespace.
1525    *
1526    *  Raw browser content => String#format_html_output => Textarea
1527    **/
1528   function format_html_output() {
1529     var text = String(this);
1530     text = text.tidy_xhtml();
1531 
1532     if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
1533       text = text.replace(/(<div>)+/g, "\n");
1534       text = text.replace(/(<\/div>)+/g, "");
1535 
1536       text = text.replace(/<p>\s*<\/p>/g, "");
1537 
1538       text = text.replace(/<br \/>(\n)*/g, "\n");
1539     } else if (Prototype.Browser.Gecko) {
1540       text = text.replace(/<p>/g, "");
1541       text = text.replace(/<\/p>(\n)?/g, "\n");
1542 
1543       text = text.replace(/<br \/>(\n)*/g, "\n");
1544     } else if (Prototype.Browser.IE || Prototype.Browser.Opera) {
1545       text = text.replace(/<p>( | |\s)<\/p>/g, "<p></p>");
1546 
1547       text = text.replace(/<br \/>/g, "");
1548 
1549       text = text.replace(/<p>/g, '');
1550 
1551       text = text.replace(/ /g, '');
1552 
1553       text = text.replace(/<\/p>(\n)?/g, "\n");
1554 
1555       text = text.gsub(/^<p>/, '');
1556       text = text.gsub(/<\/p>$/, '');
1557     }
1558 
1559     text = text.gsub(/<b>/, "<strong>");
1560     text = text.gsub(/<\/b>/, "</strong>");
1561 
1562     text = text.gsub(/<i>/, "<em>");
1563     text = text.gsub(/<\/i>/, "</em>");
1564 
1565     text = text.replace(/\n\n+/g, "</p>\n\n<p>");
1566 
1567     text = text.gsub(/(([^\n])(\n))(?=([^\n]))/, "#{2}<br />\n");
1568 
1569     text = '<p>' + text + '</p>';
1570 
1571     text = text.replace(/<p>\s*/g, "<p>");
1572     text = text.replace(/\s*<\/p>/g, "</p>");
1573 
1574     var element = Element("body");
1575     element.innerHTML = text;
1576 
1577     if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit || Prototype.Browser.Gecko) {
1578       var replaced;
1579       do {
1580         replaced = false;
1581         element.select('span').each(function(span) {
1582           if (span.hasClassName('Apple-style-span')) {
1583             span.removeClassName('Apple-style-span');
1584             if (span.className == '')
1585               span.removeAttribute('class');
1586             replaced = true;
1587           } else if (span.getStyle('fontWeight') == 'bold') {
1588             span.setStyle({fontWeight: ''});
1589             if (span.style.length == 0)
1590               span.removeAttribute('style');
1591             span.update('<strong>' + span.innerHTML + '</strong>');
1592             replaced = true;
1593           } else if (span.getStyle('fontStyle') == 'italic') {
1594             span.setStyle({fontStyle: ''});
1595             if (span.style.length == 0)
1596               span.removeAttribute('style');
1597             span.update('<em>' + span.innerHTML + '</em>');
1598             replaced = true;
1599           } else if (span.getStyle('textDecoration') == 'underline') {
1600             span.setStyle({textDecoration: ''});
1601             if (span.style.length == 0)
1602               span.removeAttribute('style');
1603             span.update('<u>' + span.innerHTML + '</u>');
1604             replaced = true;
1605           } else if (span.attributes.length == 0) {
1606             span.replace(span.innerHTML);
1607             replaced = true;
1608           }
1609         });
1610       } while (replaced);
1611 
1612     }
1613 
1614     for (var i = 0; i < element.descendants().length; i++) {
1615       var node = element.descendants()[i];
1616       if (node.innerHTML.blank() && node.nodeName != 'BR' && node.id != 'bookmark')
1617         node.remove();
1618     }
1619 
1620     text = element.innerHTML;
1621     text = text.tidy_xhtml();
1622 
1623     text = text.replace(/<br \/>(\n)*/g, "<br />\n");
1624     text = text.replace(/<\/p>\n<p>/g, "</p>\n\n<p>");
1625 
1626     text = text.replace(/<p>\s*<\/p>/g, "");
1627 
1628     text = text.replace(/\s*$/g, "");
1629 
1630     return text;
1631   }
1632 
1633   /**
1634    * String#format_html_input() -> String
1635    *
1636    *  Prepares sane HTML for editing.
1637    *
1638    *  This function preforms the reserve function of String#format_html_output. Each
1639    *  browser has difficulty editing mix formatting conventions. This restores
1640    *  most of the original browser specific formatting tags and some other
1641    *  styling conventions.
1642    *
1643    *  Textarea => String#format_html_input => Raw content
1644   **/
1645   function format_html_input() {
1646     var text = String(this);
1647 
1648     var element = Element("body");
1649     element.innerHTML = text;
1650 
1651     if (Prototype.Browser.Gecko || Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
1652       element.select('strong').each(function(element) {
1653         element.replace('<span style="font-weight: bold;">' + element.innerHTML + '</span>');
1654       });
1655       element.select('em').each(function(element) {
1656         element.replace('<span style="font-style: italic;">' + element.innerHTML + '</span>');
1657       });
1658       element.select('u').each(function(element) {
1659         element.replace('<span style="text-decoration: underline;">' + element.innerHTML + '</span>');
1660       });
1661     }
1662 
1663     if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit)
1664       element.select('span').each(function(span) {
1665         if (span.getStyle('fontWeight') == 'bold')
1666           span.addClassName('Apple-style-span');
1667 
1668         if (span.getStyle('fontStyle') == 'italic')
1669           span.addClassName('Apple-style-span');
1670 
1671         if (span.getStyle('textDecoration') == 'underline')
1672           span.addClassName('Apple-style-span');
1673       });
1674 
1675     text = element.innerHTML;
1676     text = text.tidy_xhtml();
1677 
1678     text = text.replace(/<\/p>(\n)*<p>/g, "\n\n");
1679 
1680     text = text.replace(/(\n)?<br( \/)?>(\n)?/g, "\n");
1681 
1682     text = text.replace(/^<p>/g, '');
1683     text = text.replace(/<\/p>$/g, '');
1684 
1685     if (Prototype.Browser.Gecko) {
1686       text = text.replace(/\n/g, "<br>");
1687       text = text + '<br>';
1688     } else if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
1689       text = text.replace(/\n/g, "</div><div>");
1690       text = '<div>' + text + '</div>';
1691       text = text.replace(/<div><\/div>/g, "<div><br></div>");
1692     } else if (Prototype.Browser.IE || Prototype.Browser.Opera) {
1693       text = text.replace(/\n/g, "</p>\n<p>");
1694       text = '<p>' + text + '</p>';
1695       text = text.replace(/<p><\/p>/g, "<p> </p>");
1696       text = text.replace(/(<p> <\/p>)+$/g, "");
1697     }
1698 
1699     return text;
1700   }
1701 
1702   /**
1703    * String#tidy_xhtml() -> String
1704    *
1705    *  Normalizes and tidies text into XHTML content.
1706    *   * Strips out browser line breaks, '\r'
1707    *   * Downcases tag names
1708    *   * Closes line break tags
1709    **/
1710   function tidy_xhtml() {
1711     var text = String(this);
1712 
1713     text = text.gsub(/\r\n?/, "\n");
1714 
1715     text = text.gsub(/<([A-Z]+)([^>]*)>/, function(match) {
1716       return '<' + match[1].toLowerCase() + match[2] + '>';
1717     });
1718 
1719     text = text.gsub(/<\/([A-Z]+)>/, function(match) {
1720       return '</' + match[1].toLowerCase() + '>';
1721     });
1722 
1723     text = text.replace(/<br>/g, "<br />");
1724 
1725     return text;
1726   }
1727 
1728   return {
1729     format_html_output: format_html_output,
1730     format_html_input:  format_html_input,
1731     tidy_xhtml:         tidy_xhtml
1732   };
1733 })());
1734 Object.extend(String.prototype, {
1735   /**
1736    * String#sanitize([options]) -> String
1737    * - options (Hash): Whitelist options
1738    *
1739    *  Sanitizes HTML tags and attributes. Options accepts an array of
1740    *  allowed tags and attributes.
1741    #
1742    *  "<a href='#'>Example</a>".sanitize({tags: ['a'], attributes: ['href']})
1743    **/
1744   sanitize: function(options) {
1745     return Element("div").update(this).sanitize(options).innerHTML.tidy_xhtml();
1746   }
1747 });
1748 
1749 Element.addMethods({
1750   /**
1751    * Element#sanitize([options]) -> Element
1752    * - options (Hash): Whitelist options
1753    *
1754    *  Sanitizes element tags and attributes. Options accepts an array of
1755    *  allowed tags and attributes.
1756    #
1757    *  This method is called by String#sanitize().
1758    **/
1759   sanitize: function(element, options) {
1760     element = $(element);
1761     options = $H(options);
1762     var allowed_tags = $A(options.get('tags') || []);
1763     var allowed_attributes = $A(options.get('attributes') || []);
1764     var sanitized = Element(element.nodeName);
1765 
1766     $A(element.childNodes).each(function(child) {
1767       if (child.nodeType == 1) {
1768         var children = $(child).sanitize(options).childNodes;
1769 
1770         if (allowed_tags.include(child.nodeName.toLowerCase())) {
1771           var new_child = Element(child.nodeName);
1772           allowed_attributes.each(function(attribute) {
1773             if ((value = child.readAttribute(attribute)))
1774               new_child.writeAttribute(attribute, value);
1775           });
1776           sanitized.appendChild(new_child);
1777 
1778           $A(children).each(function(grandchild) { new_child.appendChild(grandchild); });
1779         } else {
1780           $A(children).each(function(grandchild) { sanitized.appendChild(grandchild); });
1781         }
1782       } else if (child.nodeType == 3) {
1783         sanitized.appendChild(child);
1784       }
1785     });
1786     return sanitized;
1787   }
1788 });

1809

1811     this.START_TO_END   = 1;

1813     this.END_TO_START   = 3;

1859 /**
1860  * class WysiHat.Selection
1861  **/
1862 WysiHat.Selection = Class.create((function() {
1863   /**
1864    *  new WysiHat.Selection(editor)
1865    *  - editor (WysiHat.Editor): the editor object that you want to bind to
1866    **/
1867   function initialize(editor) {
1868     this.window = editor.getWindow();
1869     this.document = editor.getDocument();
1870   }
1871 
1872   /**
1873    * WysiHat.Selection#getSelection() -> Selection
1874    *  Get selected text.
1875    **/
1876   function getSelection() {
1877     return this.window.getSelection ? this.window.getSelection() : this.document.selection;
1878   }
1879 
1880   /**
1881    * WysiHat.Selection#getRange() -> Range
1882    *  Get range for selected text.
1883    **/
1884   function getRange() {
1885     var selection = this.getSelection();
1886 
1887     try {
1888       var range;
1889       if (selection.getRangeAt)
1890         range = selection.getRangeAt(0);
1891       else
1892         range = selection.createRange();
1893     } catch(e) { return null; }
1894 
1895     if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
1896       range.setStart(selection.baseNode, selection.baseOffset);
1897       range.setEnd(selection.extentNode, selection.extentOffset);
1898     }
1899 
1900     return range;
1901   }
1902 
1903   /**
1904    * WysiHat.Selection#selectNode(node) -> undefined
1905    * - node (Element): Element or node to select
1906    **/
1907   function selectNode(node) {
1908     var selection = this.getSelection();
1909 
1910     if (Prototype.Browser.IE) {
1911       var range = createRangeFromElement(this.document, node);
1912       range.select();
1913     } else if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
1914       selection.setBaseAndExtent(node, 0, node, node.innerText.length);
1915     } else if (Prototype.Browser.Opera) {
1916       range = this.document.createRange();
1917       range.selectNode(node);
1918       selection.removeAllRanges();
1919       selection.addRange(range);
1920     } else {
1921       var range = createRangeFromElement(this.document, node);
1922       selection.removeAllRanges();
1923       selection.addRange(range);
1924     }
1925   }
1926 
1927   /**
1928    * WysiHat.Selection#getNode() -> Element
1929    *  Returns selected node.
1930    **/
1931   function getNode() {
1932     var nodes = null, candidates = [], children, el;
1933     var range = this.getRange();
1934 
1935     if (!range)
1936       return null;
1937 
1938     var parent;
1939     if (range.parentElement)
1940       parent = range.parentElement();
1941     else
1942       parent = range.commonAncestorContainer;
1943 
1944     if (parent) {
1945       while (parent.nodeType != 1) parent = parent.parentNode;
1946       if (parent.nodeName.toLowerCase() != "body") {
1947         el = parent;
1948         do {
1949           el = el.parentNode;
1950           candidates[candidates.length] = el;
1951         } while (el.nodeName.toLowerCase() != "body");
1952       }
1953       children = parent.all || parent.getElementsByTagName("*");
1954       for (var j = 0; j < children.length; j++)
1955         candidates[candidates.length] = children[j];
1956       nodes = [parent];
1957       for (var ii = 0, r2; ii < candidates.length; ii++) {
1958         r2 = createRangeFromElement(this.document, candidates[ii]);
1959         if (r2 && compareRanges(range, r2))
1960           nodes[nodes.length] = candidates[ii];
1961       }
1962     }
1963 
1964     return nodes.first();
1965   }
1966 
1967   function createRangeFromElement(document, node) {
1968     if (document.body.createTextRange) {
1969       var range = document.body.createTextRange();
1970       range.moveToElementText(node);
1971     } else if (document.createRange) {
1972       var range = document.createRange();
1973       range.selectNodeContents(node);
1974     }
1975     return range;
1976   }
1977 
1978   function compareRanges(r1, r2) {
1979     if (r1.compareEndPoints) {
1980       return !(
1981         r2.compareEndPoints('StartToStart', r1) == 1 &&
1982         r2.compareEndPoints('EndToEnd', r1) == 1 &&
1983         r2.compareEndPoints('StartToEnd', r1) == 1 &&
1984         r2.compareEndPoints('EndToStart', r1) == 1
1985         ||
1986         r2.compareEndPoints('StartToStart', r1) == -1 &&
1987         r2.compareEndPoints('EndToEnd', r1) == -1 &&
1988         r2.compareEndPoints('StartToEnd', r1) == -1 &&
1989         r2.compareEndPoints('EndToStart', r1) == -1
1990       );
1991     } else if (r1.compareBoundaryPoints) {
1992       return !(
1993         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(0, r1) == 1 &&
1994         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(2, r1) == 1 &&
1995         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(1, r1) == 1 &&
1996         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(3, r1) == 1
1997         ||
1998         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(0, r1) == -1 &&
1999         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(2, r1) == -1 &&
2000         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(1, r1) == -1 &&
2001         r2.compareBoundaryPoints(3, r1) == -1
2002       );
2003     }
2004 
2005     return null;
2006   };
2007 
2008   function setBookmark() {
2009     var bookmark = this.document.getElementById('bookmark');
2010     if (bookmark)
2011       bookmark.parentNode.removeChild(bookmark);
2012 
2013     bookmark = this.document.createElement('span');
2014     bookmark.id = 'bookmark';
2015     bookmark.innerHTML = ' ';
2016 
2017     var range;
2018     if (Prototype.Browser.IE)
2019       range = new Range(this.document);
2020     else
2021       range = this.getRange();
2022     range.insertNode(bookmark);
2023   }
2024 
2025   function moveToBookmark() {
2026     var bookmark = this.document.getElementById('bookmark');
2027     if (!bookmark)
2028       return;
2029 
2030     if (Prototype.Browser.IE) {
2031       var range = this.getRange();
2032       range.moveToElementText(bookmark);
2033       range.collapse();
2034       range.select();
2035     } else if (Prototype.Browser.WebKit) {
2036       var selection = this.getSelection();
2037       selection.setBaseAndExtent(bookmark, 0, bookmark, 0);
2038     } else {
2039       var range = this.getRange();
2040       range.setStartBefore(bookmark);
2041     }
2042 
2043     bookmark.parentNode.removeChild(bookmark);
2044   }
2045 
2046   return {
2047     initialize:     initialize,
2048     getSelection:   getSelection,
2049     getRange:       getRange,
2050     getNode:        getNode,
2051     selectNode:     selectNode,
2052     setBookmark:    setBookmark,
2053     moveToBookmark: moveToBookmark
2054   };

2057 /**
2058  * class WysiHat.Toolbar
2059  **/
2060 WysiHat.Toolbar = Class.create((function() {
2061   /**
2062    * new WysiHat.Toolbar(editor)
2063    *  - editor (WysiHat.Editor): the editor object that you want to attach to
2064    *
2065    *  Creates a toolbar element above the editor. The WysiHat.Toolbar object
2066    *  has many helper methods to easily add buttons to the toolbar.
2067    *
2068    *  This toolbar class is not required for the Editor object to function.
2069    *  It is merely a set of helper methods to get you started and to build
2070    *  on top of.
2071    **/
2072   function initialize(editArea) {
2073     this.editArea = editArea;
2074 
2075     this.hasMouseDown = false;
2076     this.element = new Element('div', { 'class': 'editor_toolbar' });
2077 
2078     var toolbar = this;
2079     this.element.observe('mousedown', function(event) { toolbar.mouseDown(event); });
2080     this.element.observe('mouseup', function(event) { toolbar.mouseUp(event); });
2081 
2082     this.editArea.insert({before: this.element});
2083   }
2084 
2085   /**
2086    * WysiHat.Toolbar#addButtonSet(set) -> undefined
2087    *  - set (Array): The set array contains nested arrays that hold the
2088    *  button options, and handler.
2089    *
2090    *  Adds a button set to the toolbar.
2091    *
2092    *  WysiHat.Toolbar.ButtonSets.Basic is a built in button set,
2093    *  that looks like:
2094    *  [
2095    *    [{ name: 'bold', label: "Bold" }, function(editor) {
2096    *      editor.boldSelection();
2097    *    }],
2098    *    [{ name: 'underline', label: "Underline" }, function(editor) {
2099    *      editor.underlineSelection();
2100    *    }],
2101    *    [{ name: 'italic', label: "Italic" }, function(editor) {
2102    *      editor.italicSelection();
2103    *    }]
2104    *  ]
2105    **/
2106   function addButtonSet(set) {
2107     var toolbar = this;
2108     $A(set).each(function(button) {
2109       var options = button.first();
2110       var handler = button.last();
2111       toolbar.addButton(options, handler);
2112     });
2113   }
2114 
2115   /**
2116    * WysiHat.Toolbar#addButton(options, handler) -> undefined
2117    *  - options (Hash): Required options hash
2118    *  - handler (Function): Function to bind to the button
2119    *
2120    *  The options hash accepts two required keys, name and label. The label
2121    *  value is used as the link's inner text. The name value is set to the
2122    *  link's class and is used to check the button state.
2123    *
2124    *  toolbar.addButton({
2125    *    name: 'bold', label: "Bold" }, function(editor) {
2126    *      editor.boldSelection();
2127    *  });
2128    *
2129    *  Would create a link,
2130    *  "<a href='#' class='button bold'><span>Bold</span></a>"
2131    **/
2132   function addButton(options, handler) {
2133     options = $H(options);
2134     var button = Element('a', { 'class': 'button', 'href': '#' }).update('<span>' + options.get('label') + '</span>');
2135     button.addClassName(options.get('name'));
2136 
2137     this.observeButtonClick(button, handler);
2138     this.observeStateChanges(button, options.get('name'));
2139     this.element.appendChild(button);
2140   }
2141 
2142   /**
2143    * WysiHat.Toolbar#observeButtonClick(element, handler) -> undefined
2144    *  - element (String | Element): Element to bind handler to
2145    *  - handler (Function): Function to bind to the element
2146    *  fires wysihat:change
2147    *
2148    *  In addition to binding the given handler to the element, this observe
2149    *  function also sets up a few more events. When the elements onclick is
2150    *  fired, the toolbars hasMouseDown property will be set to true and
2151    *  back to false on exit.
2152    **/
2153   function observeButtonClick(element, handler) {
2154     var toolbar = this;
2155     $(element).observe('click', function(event) {
2156       toolbar.hasMouseDown = true;
2157       handler(toolbar.editArea);
2158       toolbar.editArea.fire("wysihat:change");
2159       Event.stop(event);
2160       toolbar.hasMouseDown = false;
2161     });
2162   }
2163 
2164   /**
2165    * WysiHat.Toolbar#observeStateChanges(element, command) -> undefined
2166    *  - element (String | Element): Element to receive changes
2167    *  - command (String): Name of editor command to observe
2168    *
2169    *  Adds the class "selected" to the given Element when the selected text
2170    *  matches the command.
2171    *
2172    *  toolbar.observeStateChanges(buttonElement, 'bold')
2173    *  would add the class "selected" to the buttonElement when the editor's
2174    *  selected text was bold.
2175    **/
2176   function observeStateChanges(element, command) {
2177     this.editArea.observe("wysihat:mousemove", function(event) {
2178       if (event.target.queryCommandState(command))
2179         element.addClassName('selected');
2180       else
2181         element.removeClassName('selected');
2182     });
2183   }
2184 
2185   /**
2186    * WysiHat.Toolbar#mouseDown(event) -> undefined
2187    *  - event (Event)
2188    *  This function is triggered when the user clicks their mouse down on
2189    *  the toolbar element. For now, it only updates the hasMouseDown property
2190    *  to true.
2191    **/
2192   function mouseDown(event) {
2193     this.hasMouseDown = true;
2194   }
2195 
2196   /**
2197    * WysiHat.Toolbar#mouseDown(event) -> undefined
2198    *  - event (Event)
2199    *  This function is triggered when the user releases their mouse from
2200    *  the toolbar element. It resets the hasMouseDown property back to false
2201    *  and refocuses on the editing window.
2202    **/
2203   function mouseUp(event) {
2204     this.editArea.focus();
2205     this.hasMouseDown = false;
2206   }
2207 
2208   return {
2209     initialize:          initialize,
2210     addButtonSet:        addButtonSet,
2211     addButton:           addButton,
2212     observeButtonClick:  observeButtonClick,
2213     observeStateChanges: observeStateChanges,
2214     mouseDown:           mouseDown,
2215     mouseUp:             mouseUp
2216   };
2217 })());

2274 /* ******************* */
2275 
2276 var SWFUpload = function (settings) {
2277 	this.initSWFUpload(settings);
2278 };
2279 
2280 SWFUpload.prototype.initSWFUpload = function (settings) {
2281 	try {
2282 		this.customSettings = {};	// A container where developers can place their own settings associated with this instance.
2283 		this.settings = settings;
2284 		this.eventQueue = [];
2285 		this.movieName = "SWFUpload_" + SWFUpload.movieCount++;
2286 		this.movieElement = null;
2287 
2288 		// Setup global control tracking
2289 		SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName] = this;
2290 
2291 		// Load the settings.  Load the Flash movie.
2292 		this.initSettings();
2293 		this.loadFlash();
2294 		this.displayDebugInfo();
2295 	} catch (ex) {
2296 		delete SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName];
2297 		throw ex;
2298 	}
2299 };

2342 // Private: initSettings ensures that all the
2343 // settings are set, getting a default value if one was not assigned.
2344 SWFUpload.prototype.initSettings = function () {
2345 	this.ensureDefault = function (settingName, defaultValue) {
2346 		this.settings[settingName] = (this.settings[settingName] == undefined) ? defaultValue : this.settings[settingName];
2347 	};
2348 	
2349 	// Upload backend settings
2350 	this.ensureDefault("upload_url", "");
2351 	this.ensureDefault("file_post_name", "Filedata");
2352 	this.ensureDefault("post_params", {});
2353 	this.ensureDefault("use_query_string", false);
2354 	this.ensureDefault("requeue_on_error", false);
2355 	
2356 	// File Settings
2357 	this.ensureDefault("file_types", "*.*");
2358 	this.ensureDefault("file_types_description", "All Files");
2359 	this.ensureDefault("file_size_limit", 0);	// Default zero means "unlimited"
2360 	this.ensureDefault("file_upload_limit", 0);
2361 	this.ensureDefault("file_queue_limit", 0);
2362 
2363 	// Flash Settings
2364 	this.ensureDefault("flash_url", "swfupload.swf");
2365 	this.ensureDefault("prevent_swf_caching", true);
2366 	
2367 	// Button Settings
2368 	this.ensureDefault("button_image_url", "");
2369 	this.ensureDefault("button_width", 1);
2370 	this.ensureDefault("button_height", 1);
2371 	this.ensureDefault("button_text", "");
2372 	this.ensureDefault("button_text_style", "color: #000000; font-size: 16pt;");
2373 	this.ensureDefault("button_text_top_padding", 0);
2374 	this.ensureDefault("button_text_left_padding", 0);
2375 	this.ensureDefault("button_action", SWFUpload.BUTTON_ACTION.SELECT_FILES);
2376 	this.ensureDefault("button_disabled", false);
2377 	this.ensureDefault("button_placeholder_id", null);
2378 	
2379 	// Debug Settings
2380 	this.ensureDefault("debug", false);
2381 	this.settings.debug_enabled = this.settings.debug;	// Here to maintain v2 API
2382 	
2383 	// Event Handlers
2384 	this.settings.return_upload_start_handler = this.returnUploadStart;
2385 	this.ensureDefault("swfupload_loaded_handler", null);
2386 	this.ensureDefault("file_dialog_start_handler", null);
2387 	this.ensureDefault("file_queued_handler", null);
2388 	this.ensureDefault("file_queue_error_handler", null);
2389 	this.ensureDefault("file_dialog_complete_handler", null);
2390 	
2391 	this.ensureDefault("upload_start_handler", null);
2392 	this.ensureDefault("upload_progress_handler", null);
2393 	this.ensureDefault("upload_error_handler", null);
2394 	this.ensureDefault("upload_success_handler", null);
2395 	this.ensureDefault("upload_complete_handler", null);
2396 	
2397 	this.ensureDefault("debug_handler", function(msg) {n2i.log(msg)});
2398 
2399 	this.ensureDefault("custom_settings", {});
2400 
2401 	// Other settings
2402 	this.customSettings = this.settings.custom_settings;
2403 	
2404 	// Update the flash url if needed
2405 	if (this.settings.prevent_swf_caching) {
2406 		this.settings.flash_url = this.settings.flash_url + "?swfuploadrnd=" + Math.floor(Math.random() * 999999999);
2407 	}
2408 	
2409 	delete this.ensureDefault;
2410 };
2411 
2412 SWFUpload.prototype.loadFlash = function () {
2413 	if (this.settings.button_placeholder_id !== "") {
2414 		this.replaceWithFlash();
2415 	} else {
2416 		this.appendFlash();
2417 	}
2418 };
2419 
2420 // Private: appendFlash gets the HTML tag for the Flash
2421 // It then appends the flash to the body
2422 SWFUpload.prototype.appendFlash = function () {
2423 	var targetElement, container;
2424 
2425 	// Make sure an element with the ID we are going to use doesn't already exist
2426 	if (document.getElementById(this.movieName) !== null) {
2427 		throw "ID " + this.movieName + " is already in use. The Flash Object could not be added";
2428 	}
2429 
2430 	// Get the body tag where we will be adding the flash movie
2431 	targetElement = document.getElementsByTagName("body")[0];
2432 
2433 	if (targetElement == undefined) {
2434 		throw "Could not find the 'body' element.";
2435 	}
2436 
2437 	// Append the container and load the flash
2438 	container = document.createElement("div");
2439 	container.style.width = "1px";
2440 	container.style.height = "1px";
2441 	container.style.overflow = "hidden";
2442 
2443 	targetElement.appendChild(container);
2444 	container.innerHTML = this.getFlashHTML();	// Using innerHTML is non-standard but the only sensible way to dynamically add Flash in IE (and maybe other browsers)
2445 };
2446 
2447 // Private: replaceWithFlash replaces the button_placeholder element with the flash movie.
2448 SWFUpload.prototype.replaceWithFlash = function () {
2449 	var targetElement, tempParent;
2450 
2451 	// Make sure an element with the ID we are going to use doesn't already exist
2452 	if (document.getElementById(this.movieName) !== null) {
2453 		throw "ID " + this.movieName + " is already in use. The Flash Object could not be added";
2454 	}
2455 	// Get the element where we will be placing the flash movie
2456 	targetElement = this.settings.button_placeholder || document.getElementById(this.settings.button_placeholder_id);
2457 
2458 	if (targetElement == undefined) {
2459 		throw "Could not find the placeholder element.";
2460 	}
2461 
2462 	// Append the container and load the flash
2463 	tempParent = document.createElement("div");
2464 	tempParent.innerHTML = this.getFlashHTML();	// Using innerHTML is non-standard but the only sensible way to dynamically add Flash in IE (and maybe other browsers)
2465 	targetElement.parentNode.replaceChild(tempParent.firstChild, targetElement);
2466 };
2467 
2468 // Private: getFlashHTML generates the object tag needed to embed the flash in to the document
2469 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashHTML = function () {
2470 	var transparent = this.settings.button_image_url === "" ? true : false;
2471 	
2472 	// Flash Satay object syntax: http://www.alistapart.com/articles/flashsatay
2473 	return ['<object id="', this.movieName, '" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" data="', this.settings.flash_url, '" width="', this.settings.button_width, '" height="', this.settings.button_height, '" class="swfupload">',
2474 				'<param name="wmode" value="', transparent ? "transparent" : "window", '" />',
2475 				'<param name="movie" value="', this.settings.flash_url, '" />',
2476 				'<param name="quality" value="high" />',
2477 				'<param name="menu" value="false" />',
2478 				'<param name="allowScriptAccess" value="always" />',
2479 				'<param name="flashvars" value="' + this.getFlashVars() + '" />',
2480 				'</object>'].join("");
2481 };
2482 
2483 // Private: getFlashVars builds the parameter string that will be passed
2484 // to flash in the flashvars param.
2485 SWFUpload.prototype.getFlashVars = function () {
2486 	// Build a string from the post param object
2487 	var paramString = this.buildParamString();
2488 
2489 	// Build the parameter string
2490 	return ["movieName=", encodeURIComponent(this.movieName),
2491 			"&uploadURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.upload_url),
2492 			"&useQueryString=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.use_query_string),
2493 			"&requeueOnError=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.requeue_on_error),
2494 			"&params=", encodeURIComponent(paramString),
2495 			"&filePostName=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_post_name),
2496 			"&fileTypes=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types),
2497 			"&fileTypesDescription=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_types_description),
2498 			"&fileSizeLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_size_limit),
2499 			"&fileUploadLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_upload_limit),
2500 			"&fileQueueLimit=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.file_queue_limit),
2501 			"&debugEnabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.debug_enabled),
2502 			"&buttonImageURL=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_image_url),
2503 			"&buttonWidth=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_width),
2504 			"&buttonHeight=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_height),
2505 			"&buttonText=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text),
2506 			"&buttonTextTopPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_top_padding),
2507 			"&buttonTextLeftPadding=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_left_padding),
2508 			"&buttonTextStyle=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_text_style),
2509 			"&buttonAction=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_action),
2510 			"&buttonDisabled=", encodeURIComponent(this.settings.button_disabled)
2511 		].join("");
2512 };
2513 
2514 // Public: getMovieElement retrieves the DOM reference to the Flash element added by SWFUpload
2515 // The element is cached after the first lookup
2516 SWFUpload.prototype.getMovieElement = function () {
2517 	if (this.movieElement == undefined) {
2518 		this.movieElement = document.getElementById(this.movieName);
2519 	}
2520 
2521 	if (this.movieElement === null) {
2522 		throw "Could not find Flash element";
2523 	}
2524 	
2525 	return this.movieElement;
2526 };
2527 
2528 // Private: buildParamString takes the name/value pairs in the post_params setting object
2529 // and joins them up in to a string formatted "name=value&name=value"
2530 SWFUpload.prototype.buildParamString = function () {
2531 	var postParams = this.settings.post_params; 
2532 	var paramStringPairs = [];
2533 
2534 	if (typeof(postParams) === "object") {
2535 		for (var name in postParams) {
2536 			if (postParams.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
2537 				paramStringPairs.push(encodeURIComponent(name.toString()) + "=" + encodeURIComponent(postParams[name].toString()));
2538 			}
2539 		}
2540 	}
2541 
2542 	return paramStringPairs.join("&");
2543 };
2544 
2545 // Public: Used to remove a SWFUpload instance from the page. This method strives to remove
2546 // all references to the SWF, and other objects so memory is properly freed.
2547 // Returns true if everything was destroyed. Returns a false if a failure occurs leaving SWFUpload in an inconsistant state.
2548 SWFUpload.prototype.destroy = function () {
2549 	try {
2550 		// Make sure Flash is done before we try to remove it
2551 		this.stopUpload();
2552 		
2553 		// Remove the SWFUpload DOM nodes
2554 		var movieElement = null;
2555 		try {
2556 			movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
2557 		} catch (ex) {
2558 		}
2559 		
2560 		if (movieElement != undefined && movieElement.parentNode != undefined && typeof movieElement.parentNode.removeChild === "function") {
2561 			var container = movieElement.parentNode;
2562 			if (container != undefined) {
2563 				container.removeChild(movieElement);
2564 				if (container.parentNode != undefined && typeof container.parentNode.removeChild === "function") {
2565 					container.parentNode.removeChild(container);
2566 				}
2567 			}
2568 		}
2569 		
2570 		// Destroy references
2571 		SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName] = null;
2572 		delete SWFUpload.instances[this.movieName];
2573 
2574 		delete this.movieElement;
2575 		delete this.settings;
2576 		delete this.customSettings;
2577 		delete this.eventQueue;
2578 		delete this.movieName;
2579 		
2580 		delete window[this.movieName];
2581 		
2582 		return true;
2583 	} catch (ex1) {
2584 		return false;
2585 	}
2586 };
2587

2640 /* Note: addSetting and getSetting are no longer used by SWFUpload but are included
2641 	the maintain v2 API compatibility
2642 */
2643 // Public: (Deprecated) addSetting adds a setting value. If the value given is undefined or null then the default_value is used.
2644 SWFUpload.prototype.addSetting = function (name, value, default_value) {
2645     if (value == undefined) {
2646         return (this.settings[name] = default_value);
2647     } else {
2648         return (this.settings[name] = value);
2649 	}
2650 };
2651 
2652 // Public: (Deprecated) getSetting gets a setting. Returns an empty string if the setting was not found.
2653 SWFUpload.prototype.getSetting = function (name) {
2654     if (this.settings[name] != undefined) {
2655         return this.settings[name];
2656 	}
2657 
2658     return "";
2659 };

2663 // Private: callFlash handles function calls made to the Flash element.
2664 // Calls are made with a setTimeout for some functions to work around
2665 // bugs in the ExternalInterface library.
2666 SWFUpload.prototype.callFlash = function (functionName, argumentArray) {
2667 	argumentArray = argumentArray || [];
2668 	
2669 	var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
2670 	var returnValue;
2671 
2672 	if (typeof movieElement[functionName] === "function") {
2673 		// We have to go through all this if/else stuff because the Flash functions don't have apply() and only accept the exact number of arguments.
2674 		if (argumentArray.length === 0) {
2675 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName]();
2676 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 1) {
2677 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0]);
2678 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 2) {
2679 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0], argumentArray[1]);
2680 		} else if (argumentArray.length === 3) {
2681 			returnValue = movieElement[functionName](argumentArray[0], argumentArray[1], argumentArray[2]);
2682 		} else {
2683 			throw "Too many arguments";
2684 		}
2685 		
2686 		// Unescape file post param values
2687 		if (returnValue != undefined && typeof returnValue.post === "object") {
2688 			returnValue = this.unescapeFilePostParams(returnValue);
2689 		}
2690 		
2691 		return returnValue;
2692 	} else {
2693 		throw "Invalid function name: " + functionName;
2694 	}
2695 };

2699 	-- Flash control methods --
2700 	Your UI should use these
2701 	to operate SWFUpload
2702    ***************************** */

2704 // Public: selectFile causes a File Selection Dialog window to appear.  This
2705 // dialog only allows 1 file to be selected. WARNING: this function does not work in Flash Player 10
2706 SWFUpload.prototype.selectFile = function () {
2707 	this.callFlash("SelectFile");
2708 };
2709 
2710 // Public: selectFiles causes a File Selection Dialog window to appear/ This
2711 // dialog allows the user to select any number of files
2712 // Flash Bug Warning: Flash limits the number of selectable files based on the combined length of the file names.
2713 // If the selection name length is too long the dialog will fail in an unpredictable manner.  There is no work-around
2714 // for this bug.  WARNING: this function does not work in Flash Player 10
2715 SWFUpload.prototype.selectFiles = function () {
2716 	this.callFlash("SelectFiles");
2717 };
