2720 // Public: startUpload starts uploading the first file in the queue unless
2721 // the optional parameter 'fileID' specifies the ID 
2722 SWFUpload.prototype.startUpload = function (fileID) {
2723 	this.callFlash("StartUpload", [fileID]);
2724 };
2725 
2726 /* Cancels a the file upload.  You must specify a file_id */
2727 // Public: cancelUpload cancels any queued file.  The fileID parameter
2728 // must be specified.
2729 SWFUpload.prototype.cancelUpload = function (fileID) {
2730 	this.callFlash("CancelUpload", [fileID]);
2731 };
2732 
2733 // Public: stopUpload stops the current upload and requeues the file at the beginning of the queue.
2734 // If nothing is currently uploading then nothing happens.
2735 SWFUpload.prototype.stopUpload = function () {
2736 	this.callFlash("StopUpload");
2737 };

2739 /* ************************
2740  * Settings methods
2741  *   These methods change the SWFUpload settings.
2742  *   SWFUpload settings should not be changed directly on the settings object
2743  *   since many of the settings need to be passed to Flash in order to take
2744  *   effect.
2745  * *********************** */
2746 
2747 // Public: getStats gets the file statistics object.
2748 SWFUpload.prototype.getStats = function () {
2749 	return this.callFlash("GetStats");
2750 };
2751 
2752 // Public: setStats changes the SWFUpload statistics.  You shouldn't need to 
2753 // change the statistics but you can.  Changing the statistics does not
2754 // affect SWFUpload accept for the successful_uploads count which is used
2755 // by the upload_limit setting to determine how many files the user may upload.
2756 SWFUpload.prototype.setStats = function (statsObject) {
2757 	this.callFlash("SetStats", [statsObject]);
2758 };
2759 
2760 // Public: getFile retrieves a File object by ID or Index.  If the file is
2761 // not found then 'null' is returned.
2762 SWFUpload.prototype.getFile = function (fileID) {
2763 	if (typeof(fileID) === "number") {
2764 		return this.callFlash("GetFileByIndex", [fileID]);
2765 	} else {
2766 		return this.callFlash("GetFile", [fileID]);
2767 	}
2768 };
2769 
2770 // Public: addFileParam sets a name/value pair that will be posted with the
2771 // file specified by the Files ID.  If the name already exists then the
2772 // exiting value will be overwritten.

2907 /* *******************************
2908 	Flash Event Interfaces
2909 	These functions are used by Flash to trigger the various
2910 	events.
2911 	
2912 	All these functions a Private.
2913 	
2914 	Because the ExternalInterface library is buggy the event calls
2915 	are added to a queue and the queue then executed by a setTimeout.
2916 	This ensures that events are executed in a determinate order and that
2917 	the ExternalInterface bugs are avoided.
2918 ******************************* */
2919 
2920 SWFUpload.prototype.queueEvent = function (handlerName, argumentArray) {
2921 	// Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
2922 	
2923 	if (argumentArray == undefined) {
2924 		argumentArray = [];
2925 	} else if (!(argumentArray instanceof Array)) {
2926 		argumentArray = [argumentArray];
2927 	}
2928 	
2929 	var self = this;
2930 	if (typeof this.settings[handlerName] === "function") {
2931 		// Queue the event
2932 		this.eventQueue.push(function () {
2933 			this.settings[handlerName].apply(this, argumentArray);
2934 		});
2935 		
2936 		// Execute the next queued event
2937 		setTimeout(function () {
2938 			self.executeNextEvent();
2939 		}, 0);
2940 		
2941 	} else if (this.settings[handlerName] !== null) {
2942 		throw "Event handler " + handlerName + " is unknown or is not a function";
2943 	}
2944 };
2945 
2946 // Private: Causes the next event in the queue to be executed.  Since events are queued using a setTimeout
2947 // we must queue them in order to garentee that they are executed in order.
2948 SWFUpload.prototype.executeNextEvent = function () {
2949 	// Warning: Don't call this.debug inside here or you'll create an infinite loop
2950 
2951 	var  f = this.eventQueue ? this.eventQueue.shift() : null;
2952 	if (typeof(f) === "function") {
2953 		f.apply(this);
2954 	}
2955 };
2956 
2957 // Private: unescapeFileParams is part of a workaround for a flash bug where objects passed through ExternalInterface cannot have
2958 // properties that contain characters that are not valid for JavaScript identifiers. To work around this
2959 // the Flash Component escapes the parameter names and we must unescape again before passing them along.
2960 SWFUpload.prototype.unescapeFilePostParams = function (file) {
2961 	var reg = /[$]([0-9a-f]{4})/i;
2962 	var unescapedPost = {};
2963 	var uk;
2964 
2965 	if (file != undefined) {
2966 		for (var k in file.post) {
2967 			if (file.post.hasOwnProperty(k)) {
2968 				uk = k;
2969 				var match;
2970 				while ((match = reg.exec(uk)) !== null) {
2971 					uk = uk.replace(match[0], String.fromCharCode(parseInt("0x" + match[1], 16)));
2972 				}
2973 				unescapedPost[uk] = file.post[k];
2974 			}
2975 		}
2976 
2977 		file.post = unescapedPost;
2978 	}
2979 
2980 	return file;
2981 };
2982 
2983 SWFUpload.prototype.flashReady = function () {
2984 	// Check that the movie element is loaded correctly with its ExternalInterface methods defined
2985 	var movieElement = this.getMovieElement();
2986 	if (typeof movieElement.StartUpload !== "function") {
2987 		throw "ExternalInterface methods failed to initialize.";
2988 	}
2989 
2990 	// Fix IE Flash/Form bug
2991 	if (window[this.movieName] == undefined) {
2992 		window[this.movieName] = movieElement;
2993 	}
2994 	
2995 	this.queueEvent("swfupload_loaded_handler");
2996 };

3029 SWFUpload.prototype.returnUploadStart = function (file) {
3030 	var returnValue;
3031 	if (typeof this.settings.upload_start_handler === "function") {
3032 		file = this.unescapeFilePostParams(file);
3033 		returnValue = this.settings.upload_start_handler.call(this, file);
3034 	} else if (this.settings.upload_start_handler != undefined) {
3035 		throw "upload_start_handler must be a function";
3036 	}
3037 
3038 	// Convert undefined to true so if nothing is returned from the upload_start_handler it is
3039 	// interpretted as 'true'.
3040 	if (returnValue === undefined) {
3041 		returnValue = true;
3042 	}
3043 	
3044 	returnValue = !!returnValue;
3045 	
3046 	this.callFlash("ReturnUploadStart", [returnValue]);
3047 };

3089 Date.parseFunctions = {count:0};
3090 Date.parseRegexes = [];
3091 Date.formatFunctions = {count:0};
3092 
3093 Date.prototype.dateFormat = function(format) {
3094     if (Date.formatFunctions[format] == null) {
3095         Date.createNewFormat(format);
3096     }
3097     var func = Date.formatFunctions[format];
3098     return this[func]();
3099 }
3100 
3101 Date.createNewFormat = function(format) {
3102     var funcName = "format" + Date.formatFunctions.count++;
3103     Date.formatFunctions[format] = funcName;
3104     var code = "Date.prototype." + funcName + " = function(){return ";
3105     var special = false;
3106     var ch = '';
3107     for (var i = 0; i < format.length; ++i) {
3108         ch = format.charAt(i);
3109         if (!special && ch == "\\") {
3110             special = true;
3111         }
3112         else if (special) {
3113             special = false;
3114             code += "'" + String.escape(ch) + "' + ";
3115         }
3116         else {
3117             code += Date.getFormatCode(ch);
3118         }
3119     }
3120     eval(code.substring(0, code.length - 3) + ";}");
3121 }
3122 
3123 Date.getFormatCode = function(character) {
3124     switch (character) {
3125     case "d":
3126         return "String.leftPad(this.getDate(), 2, '0') + ";
3127     case "D":
3128         return "Date.dayNames[this.getDay()].substring(0, 3) + ";
3129     case "j":
3130         return "this.getDate() + ";
3131     case "l":
3132         return "Date.dayNames[this.getDay()] + ";
3133     case "S":
3134         return "this.getSuffix() + ";
3135     case "w":
3136         return "this.getDay() + ";
3137     case "z":
3138         return "this.getDayOfYear() + ";
3139     case "W":
3140         return "this.getWeekOfYear() + ";
3141     case "F":
3142         return "Date.monthNames[this.getMonth()] + ";
3143     case "m":
3144         return "String.leftPad(this.getMonth() + 1, 2, '0') + ";
3145     case "M":
3146         return "Date.monthNames[this.getMonth()].substring(0, 3) + ";
3147     case "n":
3148         return "(this.getMonth() + 1) + ";
3149     case "t":
3150         return "this.getDaysInMonth() + ";
3151     case "L":
3152         return "(this.isLeapYear() ? 1 : 0) + ";
3153     case "Y":
3154         return "this.getFullYear() + ";
3155     case "y":
3156         return "('' + this.getFullYear()).substring(2, 4) + ";
3157     case "a":
3158         return "(this.getHours() < 12 ? 'am' : 'pm') + ";
3159     case "A":
3160         return "(this.getHours() < 12 ? 'AM' : 'PM') + ";
3161     case "g":
3162         return "((this.getHours() %12) ? this.getHours() % 12 : 12) + ";
3163     case "G":
3164         return "this.getHours() + ";
3165     case "h":
3166         return "String.leftPad((this.getHours() %12) ? this.getHours() % 12 : 12, 2, '0') + ";
3167     case "H":
3168         return "String.leftPad(this.getHours(), 2, '0') + ";
3169     case "i":
3170         return "String.leftPad(this.getMinutes(), 2, '0') + ";
3171     case "s":
3172         return "String.leftPad(this.getSeconds(), 2, '0') + ";
3173     case "O":
3174         return "this.getGMTOffset() + ";
3175     case "T":
3176         return "this.getTimezone() + ";
3177     case "Z":
3178         return "(this.getTimezoneOffset() * -60) + ";
3179     default:
3180         return "'" + String.escape(character) + "' + ";
3181     }
3182 }
3183 
3184 Date.parseDate = function(input, format) {
3185     if (Date.parseFunctions[format] == null) {
3186         Date.createParser(format);
3187     }
3188     var func = Date.parseFunctions[format];
3189     return Date[func](input);
3190 }
3191 
3192 Date.createParser = function(format) {
3193     var funcName = "parse" + Date.parseFunctions.count++;
3194     var regexNum = Date.parseRegexes.length;
3195     var currentGroup = 1;
3196     Date.parseFunctions[format] = funcName;
3197 
3198     var code = "Date." + funcName + " = function(input){\n"
3199         + "var y = -1, m = -1, d = -1, h = -1, i = -1, s = -1;\n"
3200         + "var d = new Date();\n"
3201         + "y = d.getFullYear();\n"
3202         + "m = d.getMonth();\n"
3203         + "d = d.getDate();\n"
3204         + "var results = input.match(Date.parseRegexes[" + regexNum + "]);\n"
3205         + "if (results && results.length > 0) {"
3206     var regex = "";
3207 
3208     var special = false;
3209     var ch = '';
3210     for (var i = 0; i < format.length; ++i) {
3211         ch = format.charAt(i);
3212         if (!special && ch == "\\") {
3213             special = true;
3214         }
3215         else if (special) {
3216             special = false;
3217             regex += String.escape(ch);
3218         }
3219         else {
3220             obj = Date.formatCodeToRegex(ch, currentGroup);
3221             currentGroup += obj.g;
3222             regex += obj.s;
3223             if (obj.g && obj.c) {
3224                 code += obj.c;
3225             }
3226         }
3227     }
3228 
3229     code += "if (y > 0 && m >= 0 && d > 0 && h >= 0 && i >= 0 && s >= 0)\n"
3230         + "{return new Date(y, m, d, h, i, s);}\n"
3231         + "else if (y > 0 && m >= 0 && d > 0 && h >= 0 && i >= 0)\n"
3232         + "{return new Date(y, m, d, h, i);}\n"
3233         + "else if (y > 0 && m >= 0 && d > 0 && h >= 0)\n"
3234         + "{return new Date(y, m, d, h);}\n"
3235         + "else if (y > 0 && m >= 0 && d > 0)\n"
3236         + "{return new Date(y, m, d);}\n"
3237         + "else if (y > 0 && m >= 0)\n"
3238         + "{return new Date(y, m);}\n"
3239         + "else if (y > 0)\n"
3240         + "{return new Date(y);}\n"
3241         + "}return null;}";
3242 
3243     Date.parseRegexes[regexNum] = new RegExp("^" + regex + "$");
3244     eval(code);
3245 }
3246 
3247 Date.formatCodeToRegex = function(character, currentGroup) {
3248     switch (character) {
3249     case "D":
3250         return {g:0,
3251         c:null,
3252         s:"(?:Sun|Mon|Tue|Wed|Thu|Fri|Sat)"};
3253     case "j":
3254     case "d":
3255         return {g:1,
3256             c:"d = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
3257             s:"(\\d{1,2})"};
3258     case "l":
3259         return {g:0,
3260             c:null,
3261             s:"(?:" + Date.dayNames.join("|") + ")"};
3262     case "S":
3263         return {g:0,
3264             c:null,
3265             s:"(?:st|nd|rd|th)"};
3266     case "w":
3267         return {g:0,
3268             c:null,
3269             s:"\\d"};
3270     case "z":
3271         return {g:0,
3272             c:null,
3273             s:"(?:\\d{1,3})"};
3274     case "W":
3275         return {g:0,
3276             c:null,
3277             s:"(?:\\d{2})"};
3278     case "F":
3279         return {g:1,
3280             c:"m = parseInt(Date.monthNumbers[results[" + currentGroup + "].substring(0, 3)], 10);\n",
3281             s:"(" + Date.monthNames.join("|") + ")"};
3282     case "M":
3283         return {g:1,
3284             c:"m = parseInt(Date.monthNumbers[results[" + currentGroup + "]], 10);\n",
3285             s:"(Jan|Feb|Mar|Apr|May|Jun|Jul|Aug|Sep|Oct|Nov|Dec)"};
3286     case "n":
3287     case "m":
3288         return {g:1,
3289             c:"m = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10) - 1;\n",
3290             s:"(\\d{1,2})"};
3291     case "t":
3292         return {g:0,
3293             c:null,
3294             s:"\\d{1,2}"};
3295     case "L":
3296         return {g:0,
3297             c:null,
3298             s:"(?:1|0)"};
3299     case "Y":
3300         return {g:1,
3301             c:"y = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
3302             s:"(\\d{4})"};
3303     case "y":
3304         return {g:1,
3305             c:"var ty = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n"
3306                 + "y = ty > Date.y2kYear ? 1900 + ty : 2000 + ty;\n",
3307             s:"(\\d{1,2})"};
3308     case "a":
3309         return {g:1,
3310             c:"if (results[" + currentGroup + "] == 'am') {\n"
3311                 + "if (h == 12) { h = 0; }\n"
3312                 + "} else { if (h < 12) { h += 12; }}",
3313             s:"(am|pm)"};
3314     case "A":
3315         return {g:1,
3316             c:"if (results[" + currentGroup + "] == 'AM') {\n"
3317                 + "if (h == 12) { h = 0; }\n"
3318                 + "} else { if (h < 12) { h += 12; }}",
3319             s:"(AM|PM)"};
3320     case "g":
3321     case "G":
3322     case "h":
3323     case "H":
3324         return {g:1,
3325             c:"h = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
3326             s:"(\\d{1,2})"};
3327     case "i":
3328         return {g:1,
3329             c:"i = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
3330             s:"(\\d{2})"};
3331     case "s":
3332         return {g:1,
3333             c:"s = parseInt(results[" + currentGroup + "], 10);\n",
3334             s:"(\\d{2})"};
3335     case "O":
3336         return {g:0,
3337             c:null,
3338             s:"[+-]\\d{4}"};
3339     case "T":
3340         return {g:0,
3341             c:null,
3342             s:"[A-Z]{3}"};
3343     case "Z":
3344         return {g:0,
3345             c:null,
3346             s:"[+-]\\d{1,5}"};
3347     default:
3348         return {g:0,
3349             c:null,
3350             s:String.escape(character)};
3351     }
3352 }
3353 
3354 Date.prototype.getTimezone = function() {
3355     return this.toString().replace(
3356         /^.*? ([A-Z]{3}) [0-9]{4}.*$/, "$1").replace(
3357         /^.*?\(([A-Z])[a-z]+ ([A-Z])[a-z]+ ([A-Z])[a-z]+\)$/, "$1$2$3");
3358 }
3359 
3360 Date.prototype.getGMTOffset = function() {
3361     return (this.getTimezoneOffset() > 0 ? "-" : "+")
3362         + String.leftPad(Math.floor(this.getTimezoneOffset() / 60), 2, "0")
3363         + String.leftPad(this.getTimezoneOffset() % 60, 2, "0");
3364 }
3365 
3366 Date.prototype.getDayOfYear = function() {
3367     var num = 0;
3368     Date.daysInMonth[1] = this.isLeapYear() ? 29 : 28;
3369     for (var i = 0; i < this.getMonth(); ++i) {
3370         num += Date.daysInMonth[i];
3371     }
3372     return num + this.getDate() - 1;
3373 }
3374 
3375 Date.prototype.getWeekOfYear = function() {
3376     // Skip to Thursday of this week
3377     var now = this.getDayOfYear() + (5 - this.getDay());
3378     // Find the first Thursday of the year
3379     var jan1 = new Date(this.getFullYear(), 0, 1);
3380     var then = (5 - jan1.getDay());
3381     return String.leftPad(((now - then) / 7) + 1, 2, "0");
3382 }
3383 
3384 Date.prototype.isLeapYear = function() {
3385     var year = this.getFullYear();
3386     return ((year & 3) == 0 && (year % 100 || (year % 400 == 0 && year)));
3387 }
3388 
3389 Date.prototype.getFirstDayOfMonth = function() {
3390     var day = (this.getDay() - (this.getDate() - 1)) % 7;
3391     return (day < 0) ? (day + 7) : day;
3392 }
3393 
3394 Date.prototype.getLastDayOfMonth = function() {
3395     var day = (this.getDay() + (Date.daysInMonth[this.getMonth()] - this.getDate())) % 7;
3396     return (day < 0) ? (day + 7) : day;
3397 }
3398 
3399 Date.prototype.getDaysInMonth = function() {
3400     Date.daysInMonth[1] = this.isLeapYear() ? 29 : 28;
3401     return Date.daysInMonth[this.getMonth()];
3402 }

3404 Date.prototype.getSuffix = function() {
3405     switch (this.getDate()) {
3406         case 1:
3407         case 21:
3408         case 31:
3409             return "st";
3410         case 2:
3411         case 22:
3412             return "nd";
3413         case 3:
3414         case 23:
3415             return "rd";
3416         default:
3417             return "th";
3418     }

3421 String.escape = function(string) {
3422     return string.replace(/('|\\)/g, "\\$1");
3423 }

3425 String.leftPad = function (val, size, ch) {
3426     var result = new String(val);
3427     if (ch == null) {
3428         ch = " ";
3429     }
3430     while (result.length < size) {
3431         result = ch + result;
3432     }
3433     return result;
3434 }

3484 /*
3485     json2.js
3486     2008-01-17
3487 
3488     Public Domain
3489 
3490     No warranty expressed or implied. Use at your own risk.
3491 
3492     See http://www.JSON.org/js.html
3493 
3494     This file creates a global JSON object containing two methods:
3495 
3496         JSON.stringify(value, whitelist)
3497             value       any JavaScript value, usually an object or array.
3498 
3499             whitelist   an optional array prameter that determines how object
3500                         values are stringified.
3501 
3502             This method produces a JSON text from a JavaScript value.
3503             There are three possible ways to stringify an object, depending
3504             on the optional whitelist parameter.
3505 
3506             If an object has a toJSON method, then the toJSON() method will be
3507             called. The value returned from the toJSON method will be
3508             stringified.
3509 
3510             Otherwise, if the optional whitelist parameter is an array, then
3511             the elements of the array will be used to select members of the
3512             object for stringification.
3513 
3514             Otherwise, if there is no whitelist parameter, then all of the
3515             members of the object will be stringified.
3516 
3517             Values that do not have JSON representaions, such as undefined or
3518             functions, will not be serialized. Such values in objects will be
3519             dropped; in arrays will be replaced with null.
3520             JSON.stringify(undefined) returns undefined. Dates will be
3521             stringified as quoted ISO dates.
3522 
3523             Example:
3524 
3525             var text = JSON.stringify(['e', {pluribus: 'unum'}]);
3526             // text is '["e",{"pluribus":"unum"}]'
3527 
3528         JSON.parse(text, filter)
3529             This method parses a JSON text to produce an object or
3530             array. It can throw a SyntaxError exception.
3531 
3532             The optional filter parameter is a function that can filter and
3533             transform the results. It receives each of the keys and values, and
3534             its return value is used instead of the original value. If it
3535             returns what it received, then structure is not modified. If it
3536             returns undefined then the member is deleted.
3537 
3538             Example:
3539 
3540             // Parse the text. If a key contains the string 'date' then
3541             // convert the value to a date.
3542 
3543             myData = JSON.parse(text, function (key, value) {
3544                 return key.indexOf('date') >= 0 ? new Date(value) : value;
3545             });
3546 
3547     This is a reference implementation. You are free to copy, modify, or
3548     redistribute.
3549 
3550     Use your own copy. It is extremely unwise to load third party
3551     code into your pages.
3552 */
3553 
3554 /*jslint evil: true */
3555 
3556 /*global JSON */
3557 
3558 /*members "\b", "\t", "\n", "\f", "\r", "\"", JSON, "\\", apply,
3559     charCodeAt, floor, getUTCDate, getUTCFullYear, getUTCHours,
3560     getUTCMinutes, getUTCMonth, getUTCSeconds, hasOwnProperty, join, length,
3561     parse, propertyIsEnumerable, prototype, push, replace, stringify, test,
3562     toJSON, toString
3563 */
3564 
3565 if (!this.JSON) {
3566 
3567     JSON = function () {
3568 
3569         function f(n) {    // Format integers to have at least two digits.
3570             return n < 10 ? '0' + n : n;
3571         }
3572 
3573         Date.prototype.toJSON = function () {
3574 
3575 // Eventually, this method will be based on the date.toISOString method.
3576 
3577             return this.getUTCFullYear()   + '-' +
3578                  f(this.getUTCMonth() + 1) + '-' +
3579                  f(this.getUTCDate())      + 'T' +
3580                  f(this.getUTCHours())     + ':' +
3581                  f(this.getUTCMinutes())   + ':' +
3582                  f(this.getUTCSeconds())   + 'Z';
3583         };
3584 
3585 
3586         var m = {    // table of character substitutions
3587             '\b': '\\b',
3588             '\t': '\\t',
3589             '\n': '\\n',
3590             '\f': '\\f',
3591             '\r': '\\r',
3592             '"' : '\\"',
3593             '\\': '\\\\'
3594         };
3595 
3596         function stringify(value, whitelist) {
3597             var a,          // The array holding the partial texts.
3598                 i,          // The loop counter.
3599                 k,          // The member key.
3600                 l,          // Length.
3601                 r = /["\\\x00-\x1f\x7f-\x9f]/g,
3602                 v;          // The member value.
3603 
3604             switch (typeof value) {
3605             case 'string':
3606 
3607 // If the string contains no control characters, no quote characters, and no
3608 // backslash characters, then we can safely slap some quotes around it.
3609 // Otherwise we must also replace the offending characters with safe sequences.
3610 
3611                 return r.test(value) ?
3612                     '"' + value.replace(r, function (a) {
3613                         var c = m[a];
3614                         if (c) {
3615                             return c;
3616                         }
3617                         c = a.charCodeAt();
3618                         return '\\u00' + Math.floor(c / 16).toString(16) +
3619                                                    (c % 16).toString(16);
3620                     }) + '"' :
3621                     '"' + value + '"';
3622 
3623             case 'number':
3624 
3625 // JSON numbers must be finite. Encode non-finite numbers as null.
3626 
3627                 return isFinite(value) ? String(value) : 'null';
3628 
3629             case 'boolean':
3630             case 'null':
3631                 return String(value);
3632 
3633             case 'object':
3634 
3635 // Due to a specification blunder in ECMAScript,
3636 // typeof null is 'object', so watch out for that case.
3637 
3638                 if (!value) {
3639                     return 'null';
3640                 }
3641 
3642 // If the object has a toJSON method, call it, and stringify the result.
3643 
3644                 if (typeof value.toJSON === 'function') {
3645                     return stringify(value.toJSON());
3646                 }
3647                 a = [];
3648                 if (typeof value.length === 'number' &&
3649                         !(value.propertyIsEnumerable('length'))) {
3650 
3651 // The object is an array. Stringify every element. Use null as a placeholder
3652 // for non-JSON values.
3653 
3654                     l = value.length;
3655                     for (i = 0; i < l; i += 1) {
3656                         a.push(stringify(value[i], whitelist) || 'null');
3657                     }
3658 
3659 // Join all of the elements together and wrap them in brackets.
3660 
3661                     return '[' + a.join(',') + ']';
3662                 }
3663                 if (whitelist) {
3664 
3665 // If a whitelist (array of keys) is provided, use it to select the components
3666 // of the object.
3667 
3668                     l = whitelist.length;
3669                     for (i = 0; i < l; i += 1) {
3670                         k = whitelist[i];
3671                         if (typeof k === 'string') {
3672                             v = stringify(value[k], whitelist);
3673                             if (v) {
3674                                 a.push(stringify(k) + ':' + v);
3675                             }
3676                         }
3677                     }
3678                 } else {
3679 
3680 // Otherwise, iterate through all of the keys in the object.
3681 
3682                     for (k in value) {
3683                         if (typeof k === 'string') {
3684                             v = stringify(value[k], whitelist);
3685                             if (v) {
3686                                 a.push(stringify(k) + ':' + v);
3687                             }
3688                         }
3689                     }
3690                 }
3691 
3692 // Join all of the member texts together and wrap them in braces.
3693 
3694                 return '{' + a.join(',') + '}';
3695             }
3696         }
3697 
3698         return {
3699             stringify: stringify,
3700             parse: function (text, filter) {
3701                 var j;
3702 
3703                 function walk(k, v) {
3704                     var i, n;
3705                     if (v && typeof v === 'object') {
3706                         for (i in v) {
3707                             if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.apply(v, [i])) {
3708                                 n = walk(i, v[i]);
3709                                 if (n !== undefined) {
3710                                     v[i] = n;
3711                                 }
3712                             }
3713                         }
3714                     }
3715                     return filter(k, v);
3716                 }
3717 
3718 
3719 // Parsing happens in three stages. In the first stage, we run the text against
3720 // regular expressions that look for non-JSON patterns. We are especially
3721 // concerned with '()' and 'new' because they can cause invocation, and '='
3722 // because it can cause mutation. But just to be safe, we want to reject all
3723 // unexpected forms.
3724 
3725 // We split the first stage into 4 regexp operations in order to work around
3726 // crippling inefficiencies in IE's and Safari's regexp engines. First we
3727 // replace all backslash pairs with '@' (a non-JSON character). Second, we
3728 // replace all simple value tokens with ']' characters. Third, we delete all
3729 // open brackets that follow a colon or comma or that begin the text. Finally,
3730 // we look to see that the remaining characters are only whitespace or ']' or
3731 // ',' or ':' or '{' or '}'. If that is so, then the text is safe for eval.
3732 
3733                 if (/^[\],:{}\s]*$/.test(text.replace(/\\./g, '@').
3734 replace(/"[^"\\\n\r]*"|true|false|null|-?\d+(?:\.\d*)?(?:[eE][+\-]?\d+)?/g, ']').
3735 replace(/(?:^|:|,)(?:\s*\[)+/g, ''))) {
3736 
3737 // In the second stage we use the eval function to compile the text into a
3738 // JavaScript structure. The '{' operator is subject to a syntactic ambiguity
3739 // in JavaScript: it can begin a block or an object literal. We wrap the text
3740 // in parens to eliminate the ambiguity.
3741 
3742                     j = eval('(' + text + ')');
3743 
3744 // In the optional third stage, we recursively walk the new structure, passing
3745 // each name/value pair to a filter function for possible transformation.
3746 
3747                     return typeof filter === 'function' ? walk('', j) : j;
3748                 }
3749 
3750 // If the text is not JSON parseable, then a SyntaxError is thrown.
3751 
3752                 throw new SyntaxError('parseJSON');
3753             }
3754         };
3755     }();
3756 }

3916 	changeState : function(state) {
3917 		if (this.state==state) return;
3918 		var objects = this.objects.values();
3919 		objects.each(function(obj) {
3920 			if (obj.state) {
3921 				if (obj.state==state) obj.show();
3922 				else obj.hide();
3923 			}
3924 		});
3925 	},
3926 	getDescendants : function(widget) {
3927 		var desc = [];
3928 		var e = widget.getElement();
3929 		if (e) {
3930 			var d = e.descendants();
3931 			var self = this;
3932 			d.each(function(node) {
3933 				self.objects.values().each(function(obj) {
3934 					if (obj.getElement()==node) {
3935 						desc.push(obj);
3936 					}
3937 				})
3938 			});
3939 		}
3940 		return desc;
3941 	},
3942 	/** Gets all ancestors of a widget
3943 		@param {Widget} A widget
3944 		@returns {Array} An array of all ancestors
3945 	*/
3946 	getAncestors : function(widget) {
3947 		var desc = [];
3948 		var e = widget.getElement();
3949 		if (e) {
3950 			var d = e.ancestors();
3951 			d.each(function(node) {
3952 				this.objects.values().each(function(obj) {
3953 					if (obj.getElement()==node) {
3954 						desc.push(obj);
3955 					}
3956 				})
3957 			}.bind(this));
3958 		}
3959 		return desc;
3960 	}

4000 }

4045 		document.body.appendChild(t);
4046 		In2iGui.toolTips[key] = t;
4047 	}
4048 	t.onclick = function() {In2iGui.hideToolTip(options)};
4049 	var n = $(options.element);

4053 	t.setStyle({'display':'block',zIndex:In2iGui.nextTopIndex()});
4054 	t.setStyle({left:(pos.left-t.getWidth()+4)+'px',top:(pos.top+2-(t.getHeight()/2)+(n.getHeight()/2))+'px'});
4055 	if (!n2i.browser.msie) {

4057 	}
4058 }

4074 In2iGui.isWithin = function(e,element) {
4075 	Event.extend(e);
4076 	var offset = element.cumulativeOffset();
4077 	var dims = element.getDimensions();
4078 	return e.pointerX()>offset.left && e.pointerX()<offset.left+dims.width && e.pointerY()>offset.top && e.pointerY()<offset.top+dims.height;
4079 }

4133 In2iGui.positionAtElement = function(element,target,options) {
4134 	options = options || {};
4135 	element = $(element);
4136 	target = $(target);
4137 	var origDisplay = element.getStyle('display');
4138 	if (origDisplay=='none') {
4139 		element.setStyle({'visibility':'hidden','display':'block'});
4140 	}
4141 	var pos = target.cumulativeOffset(),left = pos.left,top = pos.top;
4142 	var vert=options.vertical || null;
4143 	if (options.horizontal && options.horizontal=='right') {
4144 		left = left+target.getWidth()-element.getWidth();
4145 	}
4146 	if (vert=='topOutside') {
4147 		top = top-element.getHeight();
4148 	} else if (vert=='bottomOutside') {
4149 		top = top+target.getHeight();
4150 	}
4151 	left+=(options.left || 0);
4152 	top+=(options.top || 0);
4153 	element.setStyle({'left':left+'px','top':top+'px'});
4154 	if (origDisplay=='none') {
4155 		element.setStyle({'visibility':'visible','display':'none'});
4156 	}
4157 }

4162 In2iGui.getDragProxy = function() {
4163 	if (!In2iGui.dragProxy) {
4164 		In2iGui.dragProxy = new Element('div',{'class':'in2igui_dragproxy'}).setStyle({'display':'none'});
4165 		document.body.appendChild(In2iGui.dragProxy);
4166 	}
4167 	return In2iGui.dragProxy;
4168 }
4169 
4170 In2iGui.startDrag = function(e,element,options) {
4171 	var info = element.dragDropInfo;
4172 	In2iGui.dropTypes = In2iGui.findDropTypes(info);
4173 	if (!In2iGui.dropTypes) return;
4174 	var event = Event.extend(e);
4175 	var proxy = In2iGui.getDragProxy();
4176 	Event.observe(document.body,'mousemove',In2iGui.dragListener);
4177 	Event.observe(document.body,'mouseup',In2iGui.dragEndListener);
4178 	In2iGui.dragInfo = info;
4179 	if (info.icon) {
4180 		proxy.style.backgroundImage = 'url('+In2iGui.getIconUrl(info.icon,1)+')';
4181 	}
4182 	In2iGui.startDragPos = {top:event.pointerY(),left:event.pointerX()};
4183 	proxy.innerHTML = '<span>'+info.title+'</span>' || '###';
4184 	In2iGui.dragging = true;
4185 }
4186 
4187 In2iGui.findDropTypes = function(drag) {
4188 	var gui = In2iGui.get();
4189 	var drops = null;
4190 	for (var i=0; i < gui.delegates.length; i++) {
4191 		if (gui.delegates[i].dragDrop) {
4192 			for (var j=0; j < gui.delegates[i].dragDrop.length; j++) {
4193 				var rule = gui.delegates[i].dragDrop[j];
4194 				if (rule.drag==drag.kind) {
4195 					if (drops==null) drops={};
4196 					drops[rule.drop] = {};
4197 				}
4198 			};
4199 		}
4200 	}
4201 	return drops;
4202 }
4203 
4204 In2iGui.dragListener = function(e) {
4205 	var event = Event.extend(e);
4206 	In2iGui.dragProxy.style.left = (event.pointerX()+10)+'px';
4207 	In2iGui.dragProxy.style.top = event.pointerY()+'px';
4208 	In2iGui.dragProxy.style.display='block';
4209 	var target = In2iGui.findDropTarget(event.element());
4210 	if (target && In2iGui.dropTypes[target.dragDropInfo['kind']]) {
4211 		if (In2iGui.latestDropTarget) {
4212 			In2iGui.latestDropTarget.removeClassName('in2igui_drop');
4213 		}
4214 		target.addClassName('in2igui_drop');
4215 		In2iGui.latestDropTarget = target;
4216 	} else if (In2iGui.latestDropTarget) {
4217 		In2iGui.latestDropTarget.removeClassName('in2igui_drop');
4218 		In2iGui.latestDropTarget = null;
4219 	}
4220 	return false;
4221 }
4222 
4223 In2iGui.findDropTarget = function(node) {
4224 	while (node) {
4225 		if (node.dragDropInfo) {
4226 			return node;
4227 		}
4228 		node = node.parentNode;
4229 	}
4230 	return null;
4231 }
4232 
4233 In2iGui.dragEndListener = function(event) {
4234 	Event.stopObserving(document.body,'mousemove',In2iGui.dragListener);
4235 	Event.stopObserving(document.body,'mouseup',In2iGui.dragEndListener);
4236 	In2iGui.dragging = false;
4237 	if (In2iGui.latestDropTarget) {
4238 		In2iGui.latestDropTarget.removeClassName('in2igui_drop');
4239 		In2iGui.callDelegatesDrop(In2iGui.dragInfo,In2iGui.latestDropTarget.dragDropInfo);
4240 		In2iGui.dragProxy.style.display='none';
4241 	} else {
4242 		n2i.ani(In2iGui.dragProxy,'left',(In2iGui.startDragPos.left+10)+'px',200,{ease:n2i.ease.fastSlow});
4243 		n2i.ani(In2iGui.dragProxy,'top',(In2iGui.startDragPos.top-5)+'px',200,{ease:n2i.ease.fastSlow,hideOnComplete:true});
4244 	}
4245 	In2iGui.latestDropTarget=null;
4246 }

4260 /* ****************** Delegating *************** */
4261 
4262 In2iGui.extend = function(obj) {
4263 	if (!obj.name) {
4264 		In2iGui.latestObjectIndex++;
4265 		obj.name = 'unnamed'+In2iGui.latestObjectIndex;
4266 	}
4267 	In2iGui.get().objects.set(obj.name,obj);
4268 	obj.delegates = [];
4269 	obj.addDelegate = function(delegate) {
4270 		n2i.addToArray(this.delegates,delegate);
4271 	}
4272 	obj.removeDelegate = function(delegate) {
4273 		n2i.removeFromArray(this.delegates,delegate);
4274 	}
4275 	obj.fire = function(method,value,event) {
4276 		In2iGui.callDelegates(this,method,value,event);
4277 	}
4278 	if (!obj.getElement) {
4279 		obj.getElement = function() {
4280 			return this.element;
4281 		}
4282 	}
4283 	if (!obj.valueForProperty) {
4284 		obj.valueForProperty = function(p) {return this[p]};
4285 	}
4286 }
4287 
4288 In2iGui.callDelegatesDrop = function(dragged,dropped) {
4289 	var gui = In2iGui.get();
4290 	var result = null;
4291 	for (var i=0; i < gui.delegates.length; i++) {
4292 		if (gui.delegates[i]['drop$'+dragged.kind+'$'+dropped.kind]) {
4293 			gui.delegates[i]['drop$'+dragged.kind+'$'+dropped.kind](dragged,dropped);
4294 		}
4295 	}
4296 }
4297 
4298 In2iGui.callAncestors = function(obj,method,value,event) {
4299 	if (typeof(value)=='undefined') value=obj;
4300 	var d = In2iGui.get().getAncestors(obj);
4301 	d.each(function(child) {
4302 		if (child[method]) {
4303 			thisResult = child[method](value,event);
4304 		}
4305 	});
4306 }
4307 
4308 In2iGui.callDescendants = function(obj,method,value,event) {
4309 	if (typeof(value)=='undefined') value=obj;
4310 	var d = In2iGui.get().getDescendants(obj);
4311 	d.each(function(child) {
4312 		if (child[method]) {
4313 			thisResult = child[method](value,event);
4314 		}
4315 	});
4316 }
4317 
4318 In2iGui.callDelegates = function(obj,method,value,event) {
4319 	if (typeof(value)=='undefined') value=obj;
4320 	var result = null;
4321 	if (obj.delegates) {
4322 		for (var i=0; i < obj.delegates.length; i++) {
4323 			var delegate = obj.delegates[i];
4324 			var thisResult = null;
4325 			if (obj.name && delegate[method+'$'+obj.name]) {
4326 				thisResult = delegate[method+'$'+obj.name](value,event);
4327 			} else if (obj.kind && delegate[method+'$'+obj.kind]) {
4328 				thisResult = delegate[method+'$'+obj.kind](value,event);
4329 			} else if (delegate[method]) {
4330 				thisResult = delegate[method](value,event);
4331 			}
4332 			if (result==null && thisResult!=null && typeof(thisResult)!='undefined') {
4333 				result = thisResult;
4334 			}
4335 		};
4336 	}
4337 	var superResult = In2iGui.callSuperDelegates(obj,method,value,event);
4338 	if (result==null && superResult!=null) result = superResult;
4339 	return result;
4340 }
4341 
4342 In2iGui.callSuperDelegates = function(obj,method,value,event) {
4343 	if (typeof(value)=='undefined') value=obj;
4344 	var gui = In2iGui.get();
4345 	var result = null;
4346 	for (var i=0; i < gui.delegates.length; i++) {
4347 		var delegate = gui.delegates[i];
4348 		var thisResult = null;
4349 		if (obj.name && delegate[method+'$'+obj.name]) {
4350 			thisResult = delegate[method+'$'+obj.name](value,event);
4351 		} else if (obj.kind && delegate[method+'$'+obj.kind]) {
4352 			thisResult = delegate[method+'$'+obj.kind](value,event);
4353 		} else if (delegate[method]) {
4354 			thisResult = delegate[method](value,event);
4355 		}
4356 		if (result==null && thisResult!=null && typeof(thisResult)!='undefined') {
4357 			result = thisResult;
4358 		}
4359 	};
4360 	return result;
4361 }

4363 ////////////////////////////// Bindings ///////////////////////////
4364 
4365 In2iGui.firePropertyChange = function(obj,name,value) {
4366 	In2iGui.callDelegates(obj,'propertyChanged',{property:name,value:value});
4367 }
4368 
4369 In2iGui.bind = function(expression,delegate) {
4370 	if (expression.charAt(0)=='@') {
4371 		var pair = expression.substring(1).split('.');
4372 		var obj = eval(pair[0]);
4373 		var p = pair.slice(1).join('.');
4374 		obj.addDelegate({
4375 			propertyChanged : function(prop) {
4376 				if (prop.property==p) {
4377 					delegate(prop.value);
4378 				}
4379 			}
4380 		});
4381 		return obj.valueForProperty(p);
4382 	}
4383 	return expression;
4384 }

4388 In2iGui.dwrUpdate = function() {
4389 	var func = arguments[0];
4390 	var delegate = {
4391   		callback:function(data) { In2iGui.handleDwrUpdate(data) }
4392 	}
4393 	var num = arguments.length;
4394 	if (num==1) {
4395 		func(delegate);
4396 	} else if (num==2) {
4397 		func(arguments[1],delegate);
4398 	} else {
4399 		alert('Too many parameters');
4400 	}
4401 }
4402 
4403 In2iGui.handleDwrUpdate = function(data) {
4404 	var gui = In2iGui.get();
4405 	for (var i=0; i < data.length; i++) {
4406 		if (gui.objects.get(data[i].name)) {
4407 			gui.objects.get(data[i].name).updateFromObject(data[i]);
4408 		}
4409 	};
4410 }

4412 In2iGui.update = function(url,delegate) {
4413 	var dlgt = {
4414 		onSuccess:function(t) {In2iGui.handleUpdate(t,delegate)}
4415 	}
4416 	$get(url,dlgt);
4417 }
4418 
4419 In2iGui.handleUpdate = function(t,delegate) {
4420 	var gui = In2iGui.get();
4421 	var doc = t.responseXML.firstChild;
4422 	var children = doc.childNodes;
4423 	for (var i=0; i < children.length; i++) {
4424 		if (children[i].nodeType==1) {
4425 			var name = children[i].getAttribute('name');
4426 			if (name && name!='' && gui.objects.get(name)) {
4427 				gui.objects.get(name).updateFromNode(children[i]);
4428 			}
4429 		}
4430 	};
4431 	delegate.onSuccess();
4432 }

4434 In2iGui.jsonResponse = function(t,key) {
4435 	if (!t.responseXML || !t.responseXML.documentElement) {
4436 		var str = t.responseText.replace(/^\s+|\s+$/g, '');
4437 		if (str.length>0) {
4438 			var json = t.responseText.evalJSON(true);
4439 		} else {
4440 			json = '';
4441 		}
4442 		In2iGui.callDelegates(json,'success$'+key)
4443 	} else {
4444 		In2iGui.callDelegates(t,'success$'+key)
4445 	}
4446 }
4447 
4448 In2iGui.json = function(data,url,delegateOrKey) {
4449 	var options = {method:'post',parameters:{}};
4450 	if (typeof(delegateOrKey)=='string') {
4451 		options.onSuccess=function(t) {In2iGui.jsonResponse(t,delegateOrKey)};
4452 	} else {
4453 		delegate = delegateOrKey;
4454 	}
4455 	for (key in data) {
4456 		options.parameters[key]=Object.toJSON(data[key])
4457 	}
4458 	new Ajax.Request(url,options)
4459 }

4461 In2iGui.parseItems = function(doc) {
4462 	var out = [];
4463 	var items = doc.getElementsByTagName('item');
4464 	for (var i=0; i < items.length; i++) {
4465 		var item = items[i];
4466 		var title = item.getAttribute('title');
4467 		var value = item.getAttribute('value');
4468 		var icon = item.getAttribute('icon');
4469 		var kind = item.getAttribute('kind');
4470 		out.push({title:title,value:value,icon:icon,kind:kind});
4471 	}
4472 	return out;
4473 }

4475 ////////////////////////////////// Source ///////////////////////////
4476 
4477 In2iGui.Source = function(o) {
4478 	this.options = n2i.override({url:null,dwr:null},o);
4479 	this.name = o.name;
4480 	this.data = null;
4481 	this.parameters = [];
4482 	In2iGui.extend(this);
4483 	if (o.delegate) this.addDelegate(o.delegate);
4484 	this.busy=false;
4485 	In2iGui.onDomReady(this.init.bind(this));
4486 }
4487 
4488 In2iGui.Source.prototype = {
4489 	init : function() {
4490 		var self = this;
4491 		this.parameters.each(function(parm) {
4492 			parm.value = In2iGui.bind(parm.value,function(value) {
4493 				self.changeParameter(parm.key,value);
4494 			});
4495 		})
4496 		this.refresh();
4497 	},
4498 	refresh : function() {
4499 		if (this.delegates.length==0) return;
4500 		if (this.busy) {
4501 			this.pendingRefresh = true;
4502 			return;
4503 		}
4504 		this.pendingRefresh = false;
4505 		var self = this;
4506 		if (this.options.url) {
4507 			var url = new n2i.URL(this.options.url);
4508 			this.parameters.each(function(p) {
4509 				url.addParameter(p.key,p.value);
4510 			});
4511 			this.busy=true;
4512 			In2iGui.callDelegates(this,'sourceIsBusy');
4513 			new Ajax.Request(url.toString(), {onSuccess: function(t) {self.parse(t)},onException:function(t,e) {n2i.log(e)}});
4514 		} else if (this.options.dwr) {
4515 			var pair = this.options.dwr.split('.');
4516 			var facade = eval(pair[0]);
4517 			var method = pair[1];
4518 			var args = facade[method].argumentNames();
4519 			for (var i=0; i < args.length; i++) {
4520 				if (this.parameters[i])
4521 					args[i]=this.parameters[i].value || null;
4522 			};
4523 			args[args.length-1]=function(r) {self.parseDWR(r)};
4524 			this.busy=true;
4525 			In2iGui.callDelegates(this,'sourceIsBusy');
4526 			facade[method].apply(facade,args);
4527 		}
4528 	},
4529 	end : function() {
4530 		In2iGui.callDelegates(this,'sourceIsNotBusy');
4531 		this.busy=false;
4532 		if (this.pendingRefresh) {
4533 			this.refresh();
4534 		}
4535 	},
4536 	parse : function(t) {
4537 		if (t.responseXML) {
4538 			this.parseXML(t.responseXML);
4539 		}
4540 		this.end();
4541 	},
4542 	parseXML : function(doc) {
4543 		if (doc.documentElement.tagName=='items') {
4544 			this.data = In2iGui.parseItems(doc);
4545 			this.fire('itemsLoaded',this.data);
4546 		} else if (doc.documentElement.tagName=='list') {
4547 			this.fire('listLoaded',doc);
4548 		}
4549 	},
4550 	parseDWR : function(data) {
4551 		this.data = data;
4552 		this.fire('objectsLoaded',data);
4553 		this.end();
4554 	},
4555 	addParameter : function(parm) {
4556 		this.parameters.push(parm);
4557 	},
4558 	changeParameter : function(key,value) {
4559 		this.parameters.each(function(p) {
4560 			if (p.key==key) p.value=value;
4561 		})
4562 		var self = this;
4563 		window.clearTimeout(this.paramDelay);
4564 		this.paramDelay = window.setTimeout(function() {
4565 			this.refresh();
4566 		}.bind(this),100)
4567 	}
4568 }

4578 In2iGui.TextField = function(id,name,options) {
4579 	this.options = n2i.override({placeholder:null,placeholderElement:null},options);
4580 	var e = this.element = $(id);
4581 	this.element.setAttribute('autocomplete','off');
4582 	this.value = this.element.value;
4583 	this.isPassword = this.element.type=='password';
4584 	this.name = name;
4585 	In2iGui.extend(this);
4586 	this.addBehavior();
4587 	if (this.options.placeholderElement && this.value!='') {
4588 		In2iGui.fadeOut(this.options.placeholderElement,0);
4589 	}
4590 	this.checkPlaceholder();
4591 	if (e==document.activeElement) this.focused();
4592 }
4593 
4594 In2iGui.TextField.prototype = {
4595 	addBehavior : function() {
4596 		var self = this;
4597 		var e = this.element;
4598 		var p = this.options.placeholderElement;
4599 		e.observe('keyup',this.keyDidStrike.bind(this));
4600 		e.observe('focus',this.focused.bind(this));
4601 		e.observe('blur',this.checkPlaceholder.bind(this));
4602 		if (p) {
4603 			p.setStyle({cursor:'text'});
4604 			p.observe('mousedown',this.focus.bind(this)).observe('click',this.focus.bind(this));
4605 		}
4606 	},
4607 	focused : function() {
4608 		var e = this.element;
4609 		var p = this.options.placeholderElement;
4610 		if (p && e.value=='') {
4611 			In2iGui.fadeOut(p,0);
4612 		}
4613 		if (e.value==this.options.placeholder) {
4614 			e.value='';
4615 			e.removeClassName('in2igui_placeholder');
4616 			if (this.isPassword && !n2i.browser.msie) {
4617 				e.type='password';
4618 				if (n2i.browser.webkit) {
4619 					e.select();
4620 				}
4621 			}
4622 		}
4623 		e.select();		
4624 	},
4625 	checkPlaceholder : function() {
4626 		if (this.options.placeholderElement && this.value=='') {
4627 			In2iGui.fadeIn(this.options.placeholderElement,200);
4628 		}
4629 		if (this.options.placeholder && this.value=='') {
4630 			if (!this.isPassword || !n2i.browser.msie) {
4631 				this.element.value=this.options.placeholder;
4632 				this.element.addClassName('in2igui_placeholder');
4633 			}
4634 			if (this.isPassword && !n2i.browser.msie) {
4635 				this.element.type='text';
4636 			}
4637 		} else {
4638 			this.element.removeClassName('in2igui_placeholder');
4639 			if (this.isPassword && !n2i.browser.msie) {
4640 				this.element.type='password';
4641 			}
4642 		}
4643 	},
4644 	keyDidStrike : function() {
4645 		if (this.value!=this.element.value && this.element.value!=this.options.placeholder) {
4646 			this.value = this.element.value;
4647 			this.fire('valueChanged',this.value);
4648 		}
4649 	},
4650 	getValue : function() {
4651 		return this.value;
4652 	},
4653 	setValue : function(value) {
4654 		if (value==undefined || value==null) value='';
4655 		this.value = value;
4656 		this.element.value = value;
4657 	},
4658 	isEmpty : function() {
4659 		return this.value=='';
4660 	},
4661 	isBlank : function() {
4662 		return this.value.strip()=='';
4663 	},
4664 	focus : function() {
4665 		this.element.focus();
4666 	},
4667 	setError : function(error) {
4668 		var isError = error ? true : false;
4669 		this.element.setClassName('in2igui_field_error',isError);
4670 		if (typeof(error) == 'string') {
4671 			In2iGui.showToolTip({text:error,element:this.element,key:this.name});
4672 		}
4673 		if (!isError) {
4674 			In2iGui.hideToolTip({key:this.name});
4675 		}
4676 	}
4677 }

4690 In2iGui.InfoView.create = function(name,options) {

4693 	if (options.height) {
4694 		element.setStyle({height:options.height+'px','overflow':'auto','overflowX':'hidden'});
4695 	}
4696 	if (options.margin) {
4697 		element.setStyle({margin:options.margin+'px'});

4702 
4703 In2iGui.InfoView.prototype = {
4704 	addHeader : function(text) {
4705 		var row = new Element('tr');
4706 		row.insert(new Element('th',{'class' : 'in2igui_infoview_header','colspan':'2'}).insert(text));
4707 		this.body.insert(row);
4708 	},
4709 	addProperty : function(label,text) {
4710 		var row = new Element('tr');
4711 		row.insert(new Element('th').insert(label));
4712 		row.insert(new Element('td').insert(text));
4713 		this.body.insert(row);
4714 	},
4715 	addObjects : function(label,objects) {
4716 		if (!objects || objects.length==0) return;
4717 		var row = new Element('tr');
4718 		row.insert(new Element('th').insert(label));
4719 		var cell = new Element('td');
4720 		var click = this.options.clickObjects;
4721 		objects.each(function(obj) {
4722 			var node = new Element('div').insert(obj.title);
4723 			if (click) {
4724 				node.addClassName('in2igui_infoview_click')
4725 				node.observe('click',function() {
4726 					In2iGui.callDelegates(this,'objectWasClicked',obj);
4727 				});
4728 			}
4729 			cell.insert(node);
4730 		});
4731 		row.insert(cell);
4732 		this.body.insert(row);
4733 	},
4734 	setBusy : function(busy) {
4735 		if (busy) {
4736 			this.element.addClassName('in2igui_infoview_busy');
4737 		} else {
4738 			this.element.removeClassName('in2igui_infoview_busy');
4739 		}
4740 	},
4741 	clear : function() {
4742 		this.body.update();
4743 	},
4744 	update : function(data) {
4745 		this.clear();
4746 		for (var i=0; i < data.length; i++) {
4747 			switch (data[i].type) {
4748 				case 'header': this.addHeader(data[i].value); break;
4749 				case 'property': this.addProperty(data[i].label,data[i].value); break;
4750 				case 'objects': this.addObjects(data[i].label,data[i].value); break;
4751 			}
4752 		};
4753 	}
4754 }

4860 ////////////////////////////// Dragging ////////////////////////////////
4861 
4862 	startDrag : function(e) {
4863 		var event = Event.extend(e || window.event);
4864 		this.element.style.zIndex=In2iGui.nextPanelIndex();
4865 		var pos = this.element.cumulativeOffset();
4866 		this.dragState = {left:event.pointerX()-pos.left,top:event.pointerY()-pos.top};
4867 		this.latestPosition = {left: this.dragState.left, top:this.dragState.top};
4868 		this.latestTime = new Date().getMilliseconds();
4869 		var self = this;
4870 		this.moveListener = function(e) {self.drag(e)};
4871 		this.upListener = function(e) {self.endDrag(e)};
4872 		Event.observe(document,'mousemove',this.moveListener);
4873 		Event.observe(document,'mouseup',this.upListener);
4874 		event.stop();
4875 		document.body.onselectstart = function () { return false; };
4876 		return false;
4877 	},
4878 	calc : function(top,left) {
4879 		// TODO: No need to do this all the time
4880 		this.a = this.latestPosition.left-left;
4881 		this.b = this.latestPosition.top-top;
4882 		this.dist = Math.sqrt(Math.pow((this.a),2),Math.pow((this.b),2));
4883 		this.latestTime = new Date().getMilliseconds();
4884 		this.latestPosition = {'top':top,'left':left};
4885 	},
4886 	drag : function(e) {
4887 		var event = Event.extend(e);
4888 		this.element.style.right = 'auto';
4889 		var top = (event.pointerY()-this.dragState.top);
4890 		var left = (event.pointerX()-this.dragState.left);
4891 		this.element.style.top = Math.max(top,0)+'px';
4892 		this.element.style.left = Math.max(left,0)+'px';
4893 		//this.calc(top,left);
4894 		return false;
4895 	},
4896 	endDrag : function(e) {
4897 		Event.stopObserving(document,'mousemove',this.moveListener);
4898 		Event.stopObserving(document,'mouseup',this.upListener);
4899 		document.body.onselectstart = null;
4900 	}
4901 }

4921 In2iGui.Formula.prototype = {
4922 	/** @private */
4923 	addBehavior : function() {
4924 		this.element.onsubmit=function() {
4925 			this.fire('submit');
4926 			return false
4927 		}.bind(this);
4928 	},
4929 	/** Returns a map of all values of descendants */
4930 	getValues : function() {
4931 		var data = {};
4932 		var d = In2iGui.get().getDescendants(this);
4933 		for (var i=0; i < d.length; i++) {
4934 			if (d[i].options&& d[i].options.key && d[i].getValue) {
4935 				data[d[i].options.key] = d[i].getValue();
4936 			} else if (d[i].name && d[i].getValue) {
4937 				data[d[i].name] = d[i].getValue();
4938 			}
4939 		};
4940 		return data;
4941 	},
4942 	/** Returns a map of all values of descendants */
4943 	setValues : function(values) {
4944 		var d = In2iGui.get().getDescendants(this);
4945 		for (var i=0; i < d.length; i++) {
4946 			if (d[i].options && d[i].options.key) {
4947 				var key = d[i].options.key;
4948 				if (key && values[key]) {
4949 					d[i].setValue(values[key]);
4950 				}
4951 			}
4952 		}
4953 	},
4954 	/** Resets all descendants */
4955 	reset : function() {
4956 		var d = In2iGui.get().getDescendants(this);
4957 		for (var i=0; i < d.length; i++) {
4958 			if (d[i].reset) d[i].reset();
4959 		}
4960 	},
4961 	/** Adds a widget to the form */
4962 	add : function(widget) {
4963 		this.element.insert(widget.getElement());
4964 	},

4966 	 * @returns {'In2iGui.Formula.Group'} group
4967 	 */

4971 		return g;
4972 	},
4973 	/** Builds and adds a new group according to a recipe */
4974 	buildGroup : function(options,recipe) {

4977 			var w = In2iGui.Formula[item.type].create(null,item.options);
4978 			g.add(w);
4979 		});
4980 	},

4984 	}

5068 In2iGui.Formula.Text.prototype = {
5069 	addBehavior : function() {
5070 		In2iGui.addFocusClass({element:this.input,classElement:this.element,'class':'in2igui_field_focused'});
5071 		this.input.observe('keyup',this.valueMightHaveChanged.bind(this));
5072 	},
5073 	valueMightHaveChanged : function() {
5074 		if (this.input.value==this.value) return;
5075 		this.value=this.input.value;
5076 		In2iGui.callAncestors(this,'childValueChanged',this.input.value);
5077 		this.fire('valueChanged',this.input.value);
5078 	},
5079 	updateFromNode : function(node) {
5080 		if (node.firstChild) {
5081 			this.setValue(node.firstChild.nodeValue);
5082 		} else {
5083 			this.setValue(null);
5084 		}
5085 	},
5086 	updateFromObject : function(data) {
5087 		this.setValue(data.value);
5088 	},
5089 	focus : function() {
5090 		try {
5091 			this.element.focus();
5092 		} catch (ignore) {}
5093 	},
5094 	reset : function() {
5095 		this.setValue('');
5096 	},
5097 	setValue : function(value) {
5098 		this.value = value;
5099 		this.input.value = value;
5100 	},
5101 	getValue : function() {

5103 	},

5105 		return this.options.label;
5106 	},

5109 	}

5112 /********************** Dat time ***********************/
5113 
5114 In2iGui.Formula.DateTime = function(o) {
5115 	this.inputFormats = ['d-m-Y','d/m-Y','d/m/Y','d-m-Y H:i:s','d/m-Y H:i:s','d/m/Y H:i:s','d-m-Y H:i','d/m-Y H:i','d/m/Y H:i','d-m-Y H','d/m-Y H','d/m/Y H','d-m','d/m','d','Y','m-d-Y','m-d','m/d'];
5116 	this.outputFormat = 'd-m-Y H:i:s';
5117 	this.name = o.name;
5118 	this.element = $(o.element);
5119 	this.input = this.element.select('input')[0];
5120 	this.options = n2i.override({returnType:null,label:null},o);
5121 	this.value = null;
5122 	In2iGui.extend(this);
5123 	this.addBehavior();
5124 }
5125 
5126 In2iGui.Formula.DateTime.prototype = {
5127 	addBehavior : function() {
5128 		In2iGui.addFocusClass({element:this.input,classElement:this.element,'class':'in2igui_field_focused'});
5129 		this.input.observe('blur',this.check.bind(this));
5130 	},
5131 	updateFromNode : function(node) {
5132 		if (node.firstChild) {
5133 			this.setValue(node.firstChild.nodeValue);
5134 		} else {
5135 			this.setValue(null);
5136 		}
5137 	},
5138 	updateFromObject : function(data) {
5139 		this.setValue(data.value);
5140 	},
5141 	focus : function() {
5142 		try {this.input.focus();} catch (ignore) {}
5143 	},
5144 	reset : function() {
5145 		this.setValue('');
5146 	},
5147 	setValue : function(value) {
5148 		if (!value) {
5149 			this.value = null;
5150 		} else if (value.constructor==Date) {
5151 			this.value = value;
5152 		} else {
5153 			this.value = new Date();
5154 			this.value.setTime(parseInt(value)*1000);
5155 		}
5156 		this.updateUI();
5157 	},
5158 	check : function() {
5159 		var str = this.input.value;
5160 		var parsed = null;
5161 		for (var i=0; i < this.inputFormats.length && parsed==null; i++) {
5162 			parsed = Date.parseDate(str,this.inputFormats[i]);
5163 		};
5164 		this.value = parsed;
5165 		this.updateUI();
5166 	},
5167 	getValue : function() {
5168 		if (this.value!=null && this.options.returnType=='seconds') {
5169 			return Math.round(this.value.getTime()/1000);
5170 		}
5171 		return this.value;
5172 	},
5173 	getElement : function() {
5174 		return this.element;
5175 	},
5176 	getLabel : function() {
5177 		return this.options.label;
5178 	},
5179 	updateUI : function() {
5180 		if (this.value) {
5181 			this.input.value = this.value.dateFormat(this.outputFormat);
5182 		} else {
5183 			this.input.value = ''
5184 		}
5185 	}
5186 }

5210 In2iGui.Formula.DropDown.create = function(o) {

5217 
5218 In2iGui.Formula.DropDown.prototype = {
5219 	addBehavior : function() {
5220 		In2iGui.addFocusClass({element:this.element,'class':'in2igui_dropdown_focused'});
5221 		this.element.observe('click',this.clicked.bind(this));
5222 		this.element.observe('blur',this.hideSelector.bind(this));
5223 	},
5224 	updateIndex : function() {
5225 		this.items.each(function(item,i) {
5226 			if (item.value==this.value) this.index=i;
5227 		}.bind(this));
5228 	},
5229 	updateUI : function() {
5230 		if (this.items[this.index]) {
5231 			this.inner.update(this.items[this.index].title);
5232 		}
5233 		if (!this.selector) return;
5234 		this.selector.select('a').each(function(a,i) {
5235 			if (this.index==i) {
5236 				a.addClassName('in2igui_selected');
5237 			}
5238 			else a.className='';
5239 		}.bind(this));
5240 	},
5241 	clicked : function(e) {
5242 		e.stop();
5243 		this.buildSelector();
5244 		var el = this.element,s=this.selector;
5245 		el.focus();
5246 		if (!this.items) return;
5247 		In2iGui.positionAtElement(s,el,{vertical:'bottomOutside',top:-2,left:2});
5248 		s.setStyle({display:'block',width:(el.getWidth()-5)+'px',zIndex:In2iGui.nextTopIndex()});
5249 	},
5250 	getValue : function(value) {
5251 		return this.value;
5252 	},
5253 	getLabel : function() {
5254 		return this.options.label;
5255 	},
5256 	refresh : function() {
5257 		if (this.options.source) {
5258 			this.options.source.refresh();
5259 		}
5260 	},
5261 	addItem : function(item) {
5262 		this.items.push(item);
5263 		this.dirty = true;
5264 		this.updateIndex();
5265 		this.updateUI();
5266 	},
5267 	setItems : function(items) {
5268 		this.items = items;
5269 		this.dirty = true;
5270 		this.index = -1;
5271 		this.updateIndex();
5272 		this.updateUI();
5273 	},
5274 	itemsLoaded : function(items) {
5275 		this.setItems(items);
5276 	},
5277 	hideSelector : function() {
5278 		if (!this.selector) return;
5279 		this.selector.hide();
5280 	},
5281 	buildSelector : function() {
5282 		if (!this.dirty || !this.items) return;
5283 		if (!this.selector) {
5284 			this.selector = new Element('div',{'class':'in2igui_dropdown_selector'});
5285 			document.body.appendChild(this.selector);
5286 		} else {
5287 			this.selector.update();
5288 		}
5289 		var self = this;
5290 		this.items.each(function(item,i) {
5291 			var e = new Element('a',{href:'#'}).update(item.title).observe('mousedown',function(e) {
5292 				e.stop();
5293 				self.itemClicked(item,i);
5294 			})
5295 			if (i==self.index) e.addClassName('in2igui_selected');
5296 			self.selector.insert(e);
5297 		});
5298 		this.dirty = false;
5299 	},
5300 	itemClicked : function(item,index) {
5301 		this.index = index;
5302 		this.value = this.items[index].value;
5303 		this.updateUI();
5304 		this.hideSelector();
5305 	}
5306 }

5321 In2iGui.Formula.Select.create = function(name,options) {

5325 
5326 In2iGui.Formula.Select.prototype = {
5327 	addBehavior : function() {
5328 		var self = this;
5329 		this.element.observe('change',function() {
5330 			self.valueMightChange();
5331 		});
5332 	},
5333 	refresh : function() {
5334 		if (this.options.source) {
5335 			var self = this;
5336 			new Ajax.Request(this.options.source, {onSuccess: function(t) {self.update(t.responseXML)}});
5337 		}
5338 	},
5339 	update : function(doc) {
5340 		for (var i = this.element.options.length - 1; i >= 0; i--){
5341 			this.element.remove(i);
5342 		};
5343 		var items = doc.getElementsByTagName('item');
5344 		for (var i=0; i < items.length; i++) {
5345 			var title = items[i].getAttribute('title');
5346 			var value = items[i].getAttribute('value');
5347 			this.element.options[this.element.options.length] = new Option(title,value);
5348 		};
5349 		this.setValue(this.value);
5350 	},
5351 	valueMightChange : function() {
5352 		if (this.element.value!=this.value) {
5353 			this.value=this.element.value;
5354 			In2iGui.callDelegates(this,'valueDidChange',this.value);
5355 		}
5356 	},
5357 	reset : function() {
5358 		this.element.selectedIndex = 0;
5359 		this.value = null;
5360 	},
5361 	setValue : function(value) {
5362 		value=value+'';
5363 		for (var i=0; i < this.element.options.length; i++) {
5364 			if (this.element.options[i].value==value) {
5365 				this.element.selectedIndex = i;
5366 				this.value = value;
5367 				if (this.invalidValue) {
5368 					this.element.firstDescendant().remove();
5369 				}
5370 				return;
5371 			}
5372 		};
5373 		if (this.invalidValue) {
5374 			this.element.firstDescendant().value=value;
5375 		} else {
5376 			this.element.insert({top:new Element('option',{value:value})});
5377 			this.invalidValue = true;
5378 		}
5379 		this.element.selectedIndex=0;
5380 		this.value = value;
5381 	},
5382 	getValue : function(value) {
5383 		return this.element.value;
5384 	},
5385 	getLabel : function() {
5386 		return this.options.label;
5387 	}
5388 }

5491 	getValues : function() {

5493 	},

5495 		var newValues = [];
5496 		for (var i=0; i < this.values.length; i++) {
5497 			var value = this.values[i];
5498 			var found = false;
5499 			for (var j=0; j < this.subItems.length; j++) {
5500 				found = found || this.subItems[j].hasValue(value);
5501 			};
5502 			if (found) {
5503 				newValues.push(value);
5504 			}
5505 		};
5506 		this.values=newValues;

5520 		this.updateUI();
5521 	},

5524 			this.subItems[i].updateUI();
5525 		};
5526 	},

5619 In2iGui.Formula.Tokens.prototype = {

5634 		})

5647 			self.element.insert(input);
5648 			input.observe('keyup',function() {self.inputChanged(input,i)});
5649 		});
5650 	},
5651 	/** @private */
5652 	inputChanged : function(input,index) {
5653 		if (index==this.value.length-1 && input.value!=this.value[index]) {
5654 			this.addField();
5655 		}
5656 		this.value[index] = input.value;
5657 	},
5658 	/** @private */
5659 	addField : function() {
5660 		var input = new Element('input').addClassName('in2igui_tokens_token');
5661 		var i = this.value.length;
5662 		this.value.push('');
5663 		this.element.insert(input);
5664 		var self = this;
5665 		input.observe('keyup',function() {self.inputChanged(input,i)});
5666 	}

5711 	getSelection : function() {
5712 		var items = [];
5713 		for (var i=0; i < this.selected.length; i++) {
5714 			items.push(this.rows[this.selected[i]]);
5715 		};
5716 		return items;
5717 	},
5718 	getFirstSelection : function() {
5719 		var items = this.getSelection();
5720 		if (items.length>0) return items[0];
5721 		else return null;
5722 	},
5723 	setParameter : function(key,value) {
5724 		this.parameters[key]=value;
5725 	},
5726 	loadData : function(url) {
5727 		this.setUrl(url);
5728 	},
5729 	setSource : function(source) {
5730 		if (this.options.source!=source) {
5731 			this.options.source.removeDelegate(this);
5732 			source.addDelegate(this);
5733 			this.options.source = source;
5734 			source.refresh();
5735 		}
5736 	},
5737 	setUrl : function(url) {
5738 		this.url = url;
5739 		this.selected = [];
5740 		this.sortKey = null;
5741 		this.sortDirection = null;
5742 		this.window.page = 0;
5743 		this.refresh();
5744 	},
5745 	resetState : function() {
5746 		this.window = {size:null,page:0,total:0};
5747 		In2iGui.firePropertyChange(this,'state',this.window);
5748 	},
5749 	valueForProperty : function(p) {
5750 		if (p=='window.page') return this.window.page;
5751 		else if (p=='sort.key') return this.sortKey;
5752 		else if (p=='sort.direction') return (this.sortDirection || 'ascending');
5753 		else return this[p];
5754 	},
5755 	/**
5756 	 * @private
5757 	 */
5758 	refresh : function() {
5759 		if (this.options.source) {
5760 			this.options.source.refresh();
5761 			return;
5762 		}
5763 		if (!this.url) return;
5764 		var url = this.url;
5765 		if (typeof(this.window.page)=='number') {
5766 			url+=url.indexOf('?')==-1 ? '?' : '&';
5767 			url+='windowPage='+this.window.page;
5768 		}
5769 		if (this.window.size) {
5770 			url+=url.indexOf('?')==-1 ? '?' : '&';
5771 			url+='windowSize='+this.window.size;
5772 		}
5773 		if (this.sortKey) {
5774 			url+=url.indexOf('?')==-1 ? '?' : '&';
5775 			url+='sort='+this.sortKey;
5776 		}
5777 		if (this.sortDirection) {
5778 			url+=url.indexOf('?')==-1 ? '?' : '&';
5779 			url+='direction='+this.sortDirection;
5780 		}
5781 		for (key in this.parameters) {
5782 			url+=url.indexOf('?')==-1 ? '?' : '&';
5783 			url+=key+'='+this.parameters[key];
5784 		}
5785 		var self = this;
5786 		new Ajax.Request(url,{
5787 			onSuccess:function(r) {
5788 				if (r.responseXML) {
5789 					try {
5790 					self.listLoaded(r.responseXML);
5791 					} catch (e) {n2i.log(e)}
5792 				} else if (r.responseText) {
5793 					var json = r.responseText.evalJSON();
5794 					if (json.list==true) {
5795 						self.setData(json);
5796 					} else {
5797 						self.setObjects(json);
5798 					}
5799 				}
5800 			}
5801 		});
5802 	},
5803 	sort : function(index) {
5804 		var key = this.columns[index].key;
5805 		if (key==this.sortKey) {
5806 			this.sortDirection = this.sortDirection=='ascending' ? 'descending' : 'ascending';
5807 			In2iGui.firePropertyChange(this,'sort.direction',this.sortDirection);
5808 		} else {
5809 			In2iGui.firePropertyChange(this,'sort.key',key);
5810 		}
5811 		this.sortKey = key;
5812 		this.refresh();
5813 	},
5814 
5815 	/**
5816 	 * @private
5817 	 */
5818 	listLoaded : function(doc) {
5819 		this.parseWindow(doc);
5820 		this.buildNavigation();
5821 		this.body.update();
5822 		this.head.update();
5823 		this.rows = [];
5824 		this.columns = [];
5825 		var headTr = new Element('tr');
5826 		var sort = doc.getElementsByTagName('sort');
5827 		this.sortKey=null;
5828 		this.sortDirection=null;
5829 		if (sort.length>0) {
5830 			this.sortKey=sort[0].getAttribute('key');
5831 			this.sortDirection=sort[0].getAttribute('direction');
5832 		}
5833 		var headers = doc.getElementsByTagName('header');
5834 		for (var i=0; i < headers.length; i++) {
5835 			var className = '';
5836 			var th = new Element('th');
5837 			var width = headers[i].getAttribute('width');
5838 			var key = headers[i].getAttribute('key');
5839 			var sortable = headers[i].getAttribute('sortable')=='true';
5840 			if (width && width!='') {
5841 				th.style.width=width+'%';
5842 			}
5843 			if (sortable) {
5844 				var self = this;
5845 				th.in2iguiIndex = i;
5846 				th.onclick=function() {self.sort(this.in2iguiIndex)};
5847 				className+='sortable';
5848 			}
5849 			if (key==this.sortKey) {
5850 				className+=' sort_'+this.sortDirection;
5851 			}
5852 			th.className=className;
5853 			var span = new Element('span');
5854 			th.appendChild(span);
5855 			span.appendChild(document.createTextNode(headers[i].getAttribute('title')));
5856 			headTr.appendChild(th);
5857 			this.columns.push({'key':key,'sortable':sortable,'width':width});
5858 		};
5859 		this.head.appendChild(headTr);
5860 		var rows = doc.getElementsByTagName('row');
5861 		for (var i=0; i < rows.length; i++) {
5862 			var cells = rows[i].getElementsByTagName('cell');
5863 			var row = new Element('tr');
5864 			var icon = rows[i].getAttribute('icon');
5865 			var title = rows[i].getAttribute('title');
5866 			for (var j=0; j < cells.length; j++) {
5867 				var td = new Element('td');
5868 				this.parseCell(cells[j],td);
5869 				row.insert(td);
5870 				if (!title) title = cells[j].innerText;
5871 				if (!icon && cells[j].getAttribute('icon')) icon = cells[j].getAttribute('icon');
5872 			};
5873 			var info = {id:rows[i].getAttribute('id'),kind:rows[i].getAttribute('kind'),icon:icon,title:title,index:i};
5874 			row.dragDropInfo = info;
5875 			this.addRowBehavior(row,i);
5876 			this.body.insert(row);
5877 			this.rows.push(info);
5878 		};
5879 	},
5880 	
5881 	objectsLoaded : function(data) {
5882 		if (data.constructor == Array) {
5883 			this.setObjects(data);
5884 		} else {
5885 			this.setData(data);
5886 		}
5887 	},
5888 	sourceIsBusy : function() {
5889 		this.element.addClassName('in2igui_list_busy');
5890 	},
5891 	sourceIsNotBusy : function() {
5892 		this.element.removeClassName('in2igui_list_busy');
5893 	}
5894 };
5895 
5896 In2iGui.List.prototype.filter = function(str) {
5897 	var len = 20;
5898 	var regex = new RegExp("[\\w]{"+len+",}","g");
5899 	var match = regex.exec(str);
5900 	if (match) {
5901 		for (var i=0; i < match.length; i++) {
5902 			var rep = '';
5903 			for (var j=0; j < match[i].length; j++) {
5904 				rep+=match[i][j];
5905 				if ((j+1)%len==0) rep+='\u200B';
5906 			};
5907 			str = str.replace(match[i],rep);
5908 		};
5909 	}
5910 	return str;
5911 }
5912 
5913 In2iGui.List.prototype.parseCell = function(node,cell) {
5914 	if (node.getAttribute('icon')!=null) {
5915 		var icon = new Element('div',{'class':'icon'}).setStyle({'backgroundImage':'url("'+In2iGui.getIconUrl(node.getAttribute('icon'),1)+'")'});
5916 		cell.insert(icon);
5917 	}
5918 	for (var i=0; i < node.childNodes.length; i++) {
5919 		var child = node.childNodes[i];
5920 		if (child.nodeType==n2i.TEXT_NODE && child.nodeValue.length>0) {
5921 			cell.appendChild(document.createTextNode(child.nodeValue));
5922 		} else if (child.nodeType==n2i.ELEMENT_NODE && child.nodeName=='break') {
5923 			cell.insert(new Element('br'));
5924 		} else if (child.nodeType==n2i.ELEMENT_NODE && child.nodeName=='object') {
5925 			var obj = new Element('div',{'class':'object'});
5926 			if (child.getAttribute('icon')!=null) {
5927 				var icon = new Element('div',{'class':'icon'}).setStyle({'backgroundImage':'url("'+In2iGui.getIconUrl(child.getAttribute('icon'),1)+'")'});
5928 				obj.insert(icon);
5929 			}
5930 			if (child.firstChild && child.firstChild.nodeType==n2i.TEXT_NODE && child.firstChild.nodeValue.length>0) {
5931 				obj.appendChild(document.createTextNode(child.firstChild.nodeValue));
5932 			}
5933 			cell.insert(obj);
5934 		}
5935 	};
5936 }
5937 
5938 /**
5939  * @private
5940  */
5941 In2iGui.List.prototype.parseWindow = function(doc) {
5942 	var wins = doc.getElementsByTagName('window');
5943 	if (wins.length>0) {
5944 		var win = wins[0];
5945 		this.window.total = parseInt(win.getAttribute('total'));
5946 		this.window.size = parseInt(win.getAttribute('size'));
5947 		this.window.page = parseInt(win.getAttribute('page'));
5948 	} else {
5949 		this.window.total = 0;
5950 		this.window.size = 0;
5951 		this.window.page = 0;
5952 	}
5953 }
5954 
5955 In2iGui.List.prototype.buildNavigation = function() {
5956 	var self = this;
5957 	var pages = this.window.size>0 ? Math.ceil(this.window.total/this.window.size) : 0;
5958 	if (pages<2) {
5959 		this.navigation.style.display='none';
5960 		return;
5961 	}
5962 	this.navigation.style.display='block';
5963 	var from = ((this.window.page)*this.window.size+1);
5964 	this.count.update('<span><span>'+from+'-'+Math.min((this.window.page+1)*this.window.size,this.window.total)+'/'+this.window.total+'</span></span>');
5965 	this.windowPageBody.update();
5966 	if (pages<2) {
5967 		this.windowPage.style.display='none';	
5968 	} else {
5969 		for (var i=0;i<pages;i++) {
5970 			var a = document.createElement('a');
5971 			a.appendChild(document.createTextNode(i+1));
5972 			a.in2GuiPage = i;
5973 			a.onclick = function() {
5974 				self.windowPageWasClicked(this);
5975 				return false;
5976 			}
5977 			if (i==this.window.page) {
5978 				a.className='selected';
5979 			}
5980 			this.windowPageBody.appendChild(a);
5981 		}
5982 		this.windowPage.style.display='block';
5983 	}
5984 }

5988 In2iGui.List.prototype.setData = function(data) {
5989 	this.selected = [];
5990 	var win = data.window || {};
5991 	this.window.total = win.total || 0;
5992 	this.window.size = win.size || 0;
5993 	this.window.page = win.page || 0;
5994 	this.buildNavigation();
5995 	this.buildHeaders(data.headers);
5996 	this.buildRows(data.rows);
5997 },

5999 In2iGui.List.prototype.buildHeaders = function(headers) {
6000 	var self = this;
6001 	this.head.update();
6002 	this.columns = [];
6003 	var tr = new Element('tr');
6004 	this.head.insert(tr);
6005 	headers.each(function(h,i) {
6006 		var th = new Element('th');
6007 		var style = {};
6008 		if (h.width) th.setStyle({width:h.width+'%'});
6009 		if (h.sortable) {
6010 			th.observe('click',function() {self.sort(i)});
6011 			th.addClassName('sortable');
6012 		}
6013 		th.insert(new Element('span').update(h.title));
6014 		tr.insert(th);
6015 		self.columns.push(h);
6016 	});
6017 }

6019 In2iGui.List.prototype.buildRows = function(rows) {
6020 	var self = this;
6021 	this.body.update();
6022 	//this.body = new Element('tbody');
6023 	this.rows = [];
6024 	if (!rows) return;
6025 	rows.each(function(r,i) {
6026 		var tr = new Element('tr');
6027 		var icon = r.icon;
6028 		var title = r.title;
6029 		r.cells.each(function(c) {
6030 			var td = new Element('td');
6031 			if (c.icon) {
6032 				var icn = new Element('div',{'class':'icon'}).setStyle({'backgroundImage':'url("'+In2iGui.getIconUrl(c.icon,1)+'")'});
6033 				td.insert(icn);
6034 				icon = icon || c.icon;
6035 			}
6036 			if (c.text) {
6037 				td.insert(c.text);
6038 				title = title || c.text;
6039 			}
6040 			tr.insert(td);
6041 		})
6042 		self.body.insert(tr);
6043 		var info = {id:r.id,kind:r.kind,icon:icon,title:title,index:i};
6044 		tr.dragDropInfo = info;
6045 		self.addRowBehavior(tr,i);
6046 		self.rows.push(info);
6047 	})
6048 	//this.table.insert(this.body);
6049 }

6054 In2iGui.List.prototype.setObjects = function(objects) {
6055 	this.selected = [];
6056 	this.body.update();
6057 	this.rows = [];
6058 	for (var i=0; i < objects.length; i++) {
6059 		var row = new Element('tr');
6060 		var obj = objects[i];
6061 		for (var j=0; j < this.columns.length; j++) {
6062 			var cell = new Element('td');
6063 			if (this.builder) {
6064 				cell.update(this.builder.buildColumn(this.columns[j],obj));
6065 			} else {
6066 				var value = obj[this.columns[j].key] || '';
6067 				if (value.constructor == Array) {
6068 					for (var k=0; k < value.length; k++) {
6069 						if (value[k].constructor == Object) {
6070 							cell.insert(this.createObject(value[k]));
6071 						} else {
6072 							cell.insert(new Element('div').update(value));
6073 						}
6074 					};
6075 				} else if (value.constructor == Object) {
6076 					cell.insert(this.createObject(value[j]));
6077 				} else {
6078 					cell.insert(value);
6079 				}
6080 			}
6081 			row.insert(cell);
6082 		};
6083 		this.body.insert(row);
6084 		this.addRowBehavior(row,i);
6085 		this.rows.push(obj);
6086 	};
6087 }
6088 
6089 In2iGui.List.prototype.createObject = function(object) {
6090 	var node = new Element('div',{'class':'object'});
6091 	if (object.icon) {
6092 		node.insert(new Element('div',{'class':'icon'}).setStyle({'backgroundImage':'url("'+In2iGui.getIconUrl(object.icon,1)+'")'}));
6093 	}
6094 	return node.insert(object.text || object.name || '');
6095 }

6227 In2iGui.ObjectList.prototype = {
6228 	ignite : function() {
6229 		this.addObject({});
6230 	},
6231 	addObject : function(data,addToEnd) {
6232 		if (this.objects.length==0 || addToEnd) {
6233 			var obj = new In2iGui.ObjectList.Object(this.objects.length,data,this);
6234 			this.objects.push(obj);
6235 			this.body.appendChild(obj.getElement());
6236 		} else {
6237 			var last = this.objects.pop();
6238 			var obj = new In2iGui.ObjectList.Object(last.index,data,this);
6239 			last.index++;
6240 			this.objects.push(obj);
6241 			this.objects.push(last);
6242 			this.body.insertBefore(obj.getElement(),last.getElement())
6243 		}
6244 	},
6245 	reset : function() {
6246 		for (var i=0; i < this.objects.length; i++) {
6247 			var element = this.objects[i].getElement();
6248 			element.parentNode.removeChild(element);
6249 		};
6250 		this.objects = [];
6251 		this.addObject({});
6252 	},
6253 	addObjects : function(data) {
6254 		for (var i=0; i < data.length; i++) {
6255 			this.addObject(data[i]);
6256 		};
6257 	},
6258 	setObjects : function(data) {
6259 		this.reset();
6260 		this.addObjects(data);
6261 	},
6262 	getObjects : function(data) {
6263 		var list = [];
6264 		for (var i=0; i < this.objects.length-1; i++) {
6265 			list.push(this.objects[i].getData());
6266 		};
6267 		return list;
6268 	},
6269 	getValue : function() {
6270 		return this.getObjects();
6271 	},
6272 	setValue : function(data) {
6273 		this.setObjects(data);
6274 	},
6275 	registerTemplateItem : function(item) {
6276 		this.template.push(item);
6277 	},
6278 	objectDidChange : function(obj) {
6279 		if (obj.index>=this.objects.length-1) {
6280 			this.addObject({},true);
6281 		}
6282 	}
6283 }

6287 In2iGui.ObjectList.Object = function(index,data,list) {
6288 	this.data = data;
6289 	this.index = index;
6290 	this.list = list;
6291 	this.fields = [];
6292 }
6293 
6294 In2iGui.ObjectList.Object.prototype = {
6295 	getElement : function() {
6296 		if (!this.element) {
6297 			var self = this;
6298 			this.element = document.createElement('tr');
6299 			for (var i=0; i < this.list.template.length; i++) {
6300 				var template = this.list.template[i];
6301 				var field = template.clone();
6302 				field.object = this;
6303 				this.fields.push(field);
6304 				var cell = document.createElement('td');
6305 				if (i==0) cell.className='first';
6306 				cell.appendChild(field.getElement());
6307 				field.setValue(this.data[template.key]);
6308 				this.element.appendChild(cell);
6309 			};
6310 		}
6311 		return this.element;
6312 	},
6313 	valueDidChange : function() {
6314 		this.list.objectDidChange(this);
6315 	},
6316 	getData : function() {
6317 		var data = this.data;
6318 		for (var i=0; i < this.fields.length; i++) {
6319 			data[this.fields[i].key] = this.fields[i].getValue();
6320 		};
6321 		return data;
6322 	}
6323 }

6414

6423 		obj.setVariant(options.variant);
6424 	}

6429 		obj.setTitle(options.title);
6430 	}
